56#ifdef V8_ENABLE_HEAP_SNAPSHOT_VERIFY
57class HeapEntryVerifier {
58 public:
59 HeapEntryVerifier(HeapSnapshotGenerator* generator, Tagged<HeapObject> obj)
60 : generator_(generator),
61 primary_object_(obj),
62 reference_summary_(
63 ReferenceSummary::SummarizeReferencesFrom(generator->heap(), obj)) {
64 generator->set_verifier(this);
65 }
66 ~HeapEntryVerifier() {
67 CheckAllReferencesWereChecked();
68 generator_->set_verifier(nullptr);
69 }
70
71 // Checks that `host` retains `target`, according to the marking visitor. This
72 // allows us to verify, when adding edges to the snapshot, that they
73 // correspond to real retaining relationships.
74 void CheckStrongReference(Tagged<HeapObject> host,
75 Tagged<HeapObject> target) {
76 // All references should be from the current primary object.
77 CHECK_EQ(host, primary_object_);
78
79 checked_objects_.insert(target);
80
81 // Check whether there is a direct strong reference from host to target.
82 if (reference_summary_.strong_references().find(target) !=
83 reference_summary_.strong_references().end()) {
84 return;
85 }
86
87 // There is no direct reference from host to target, but sometimes heap
88 // snapshots include references that skip one, two, or three objects, such
89 // as __proto__ on a JSObject referring to its Map's prototype, or a
90 // property getter that bypasses the property array and accessor info. At
91 // this point, we must check for those indirect references.
92 for (size_t level = 0; level < 3; ++level) {
93 const UnorderedHeapObjectSet& indirect =
94 GetIndirectStrongReferences(level);
95 if (indirect.find(target) != indirect.end()) {
96 return;
97 }
98 }
99
100 FATAL("Could not find any matching reference");
101 }
102
103 // Checks that `host` has a weak reference to `target`, according to the
104 // marking visitor.
105 void CheckWeakReference(Tagged<HeapObject> host, Tagged<HeapObject> target) {
106 // All references should be from the current primary object.
107 CHECK_EQ(host, primary_object_);
108
109 checked_objects_.insert(target);
110 CHECK_NE(reference_summary_.weak_references().find(target),
111 reference_summary_.weak_references().end());
112 }
113
114 // Marks the relationship between `host` and `target` as checked, even if the
115 // marking visitor found no such relationship. This is necessary for
116 // ephemerons, where a pair of objects is required to retain the target.
117 // Use this function with care, since it bypasses verification.
118 void MarkReferenceCheckedWithoutChecking(Tagged<HeapObject> host,
119 Tagged<HeapObject> target) {
120 if (host == primary_object_) {
121 checked_objects_.insert(target);
122 }
123 }
124
125 // Verifies that all of the references found by the marking visitor were
126 // checked via a call to CheckStrongReference or CheckWeakReference, or
127 // deliberately skipped via a call to MarkReferenceCheckedWithoutChecking.
128 // This ensures that there aren't retaining relationships found by the marking
129 // visitor which were omitted from the heap snapshot.
130 void CheckAllReferencesWereChecked() {
131 // Both loops below skip pointers to read-only objects, because the heap
132 // snapshot deliberately omits many of those (see IsEssentialObject).
133 // Read-only objects can't ever retain normal read-write objects, so these
134 // are fine to skip.
135 for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj : reference_summary_.strong_references()) {
136 if (!MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(obj)->InReadOnlySpace()) {
137 CHECK_NE(checked_objects_.find(obj), checked_objects_.end());
138 }
139 }
140 for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj : reference_summary_.weak_references()) {
141 if (!MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(obj)->InReadOnlySpace()) {
142 CHECK_NE(checked_objects_.find(obj), checked_objects_.end());
143 }
144 }
145 }
146
147 private:
148 using UnorderedHeapObjectSet =
149 std::unordered_set<Tagged<HeapObject>, Object::Hasher,
150 Object::KeyEqualSafe>;
151
152 const UnorderedHeapObjectSet& GetIndirectStrongReferences(size_t level) {
153 CHECK_GE(indirect_strong_references_.size(), level);
154
155 if (indirect_strong_references_.size() == level) {
156 // Expansion is needed.
157 indirect_strong_references_.resize(level + 1);
158 const UnorderedHeapObjectSet& previous =
159 level == 0 ? reference_summary_.strong_references()
160 : indirect_strong_references_[level - 1];
161 for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj : previous) {
162 if (MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(obj)->InReadOnlySpace()) {
163 // Marking visitors don't expect to visit objects in read-only space,
164 // and will fail DCHECKs if they are used on those objects. Read-only
165 // objects can never retain anything outside read-only space, so
166 // skipping those objects doesn't weaken verification.
167 continue;
168 }
169
170 // Indirect references should only bypass internal structures, not
171 // user-visible objects or contexts.
172 if (IsJSReceiver(obj) || IsString(obj) || IsContext(obj)) {
173 continue;
174 }
175
176 ReferenceSummary summary =
177 ReferenceSummary::SummarizeReferencesFrom(generator_->heap(), obj);
178 indirect_strong_references_[level].insert(
179 summary.strong_references().begin(),
180 summary.strong_references().end());
181 }
182 }
183
184 return indirect_strong_references_[level];
185 }
186
187 DISALLOW_GARBAGE_COLLECTION(no_gc)
188 HeapSnapshotGenerator* generator_;
189 Tagged<HeapObject> primary_object_;
190
191 // All objects referred to by primary_object_, according to a marking visitor.
192 ReferenceSummary reference_summary_;
193
194 // Objects that have been checked via a call to CheckStrongReference or
195 // CheckWeakReference, or deliberately skipped via a call to
196 // MarkReferenceCheckedWithoutChecking.
197 std::unordered_set<Tagged<HeapObject>, Object::Hasher, Object::KeyEqualSafe>
198 checked_objects_;
199
200 // Objects transitively retained by the primary object. The objects in the set
201 // at index i are retained by the primary object via a chain of i+1
202 // intermediate objects.
203 std::vector<UnorderedHeapObjectSet> indirect_strong_references_;
204};
205#endif

208 HeapEntry* to)
209 : bit_field_(TypeField::encode(type) |

240void HeapEntry::VerifyReference(HeapGraphEdge::Type type, HeapEntry* entry,
241 HeapSnapshotGenerator* generator,
242 ReferenceVerification verification) {
243#ifdef V8_ENABLE_HEAP_SNAPSHOT_VERIFY
244 if (verification == kOffHeapPointer || generator->verifier() == nullptr) {
245 // Off-heap pointers are outside the scope of this verification; we just
246 // trust the embedder to provide accurate data. If the verifier is null,
247 // then verification is disabled.
248 return;
249 }
250 if (verification == kCustomWeakPointer) {
251 // The caller declared that this is a weak pointer ignored by the marking
252 // visitor. All we can verify at this point is that the edge type declares
253 // it to be weak.
254 CHECK_EQ(type, HeapGraphEdge::kWeak);
255 return;
256 }
257 Address from_address =
258 reinterpret_cast<Address>(generator->FindHeapThingForHeapEntry(this));
259 Address to_address =
260 reinterpret_cast<Address>(generator->FindHeapThingForHeapEntry(entry));
261 if (from_address == kNullAddress || to_address == kNullAddress) {
262 // One of these entries doesn't correspond to a real heap object.
263 // Verification is not possible.
264 return;
265 }
266 Tagged<HeapObject> from_obj = Cast<HeapObject>(Tagged<Object>(from_address));
267 Tagged<HeapObject> to_obj = Cast<HeapObject>(Tagged<Object>(to_address));
268 if (MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(to_obj)->InReadOnlySpace()) {
269 // We can't verify pointers into read-only space, because marking visitors
270 // might not mark those. For example, every Map has a pointer to the
271 // MetaMap, but marking visitors don't bother with following that link.
272 // Read-only objects are immortal and can never point to things outside of
273 // read-only space, so ignoring these objects is safe from the perspective
274 // of ensuring accurate retaining paths for normal read-write objects.
275 // Therefore, do nothing.
276 } else if (verification == kEphemeron) {
277 // Ephemerons can't be verified because they aren't marked directly by the
278 // marking visitor.
279 generator->verifier()->MarkReferenceCheckedWithoutChecking(from_obj,
280 to_obj);
281 } else if (type == HeapGraphEdge::kWeak) {
282 generator->verifier()->CheckWeakReference(from_obj, to_obj);
283 } else {
284 generator->verifier()->CheckStrongReference(from_obj, to_obj);
285 }
286#endif
287}

289void HeapEntry::SetNamedReference(HeapGraphEdge::Type type, const char* name,
290 HeapEntry* entry,
291 HeapSnapshotGenerator* generator,
292 ReferenceVerification verification) {
293 ++children_count_;
294 snapshot_->edges().emplace_back(type, name, this, entry);
295 VerifyReference(type, entry, generator, verification);
296}

307void HeapEntry::SetNamedAutoIndexReference(HeapGraphEdge::Type type,
308 const char* description,

320void HeapEntry::Print(const char* prefix, const char* edge_name, int max_depth,
321 int indent) const {
322 static_assert(sizeof(unsigned) == sizeof(id()));
323 base::OS::Print("%6zu @%6u %*c %s%s: ", self_size(), id(), indent, ' ',
324 prefix, edge_name);
325 if (type() != kString) {
326 base::OS::Print("%s %.40s\n", TypeAsString(), name_);
327 } else {
328 base::OS::Print("\"");
329 const char* c = name_;
330 while (*c && (c - name_) <= 40) {
331 if (*c != '\n')
332 base::OS::Print("%c", *c);
333 else
334 base::OS::Print("\\n");
335 ++c;
336 }
337 base::OS::Print("\"\n");
338 }
339 if (--max_depth == 0) return;
340 for (auto i = children_begin(); i != children_end(); ++i) {
341 HeapGraphEdge& edge = **i;
342 const char* edge_prefix = "";
343 base::EmbeddedVector<char, 64> index;
344 edge_name = index.begin();
345 switch (edge.type()) {
346 case HeapGraphEdge::kContextVariable:
347 edge_prefix = "#";
348 edge_name = edge.name();
349 break;
350 case HeapGraphEdge::kElement:
351 SNPrintF(index, "%d", edge.index());
352 break;
353 case HeapGraphEdge::kInternal:
354 edge_prefix = "$";
355 edge_name = edge.name();
356 break;
357 case HeapGraphEdge::kProperty:
358 edge_name = edge.name();
359 break;
360 case HeapGraphEdge::kHidden:
361 edge_prefix = "$";
362 SNPrintF(index, "%d", edge.index());
363 break;
364 case HeapGraphEdge::kShortcut:
365 edge_prefix = "^";
366 edge_name = edge.name();
367 break;
368 case HeapGraphEdge::kWeak:
369 edge_prefix = "w";
370 edge_name = edge.name();
371 break;
372 default:
373 SNPrintF(index, "!!! unknown edge type: %d ", edge.type());
374 }
375 edge.to()->Print(edge_prefix, edge_name, max_depth, indent + 2);
376 }
377}

379const char* HeapEntry::TypeAsString() const {
380 switch (type()) {
381 case kHidden:
382 return "/hidden/";
383 case kObject:
384 return "/object/";
385 case kClosure:
386 return "/closure/";
387 case kString:
388 return "/string/";
389 case kCode:
390 return "/code/";
391 case kArray:
392 return "/array/";
393 case kRegExp:
394 return "/regexp/";
395 case kHeapNumber:
396 return "/number/";
397 case kNative:
398 return "/native/";
399 case kSynthetic:
400 return "/synthetic/";
401 case kConsString:
402 return "/concatenated string/";
403 case kSlicedString:
404 return "/sliced string/";
405 case kSymbol:
406 return "/symbol/";
407 case kBigInt:
408 return "/bigint/";
409 case kObjectShape:
410 return "/object shape/";
411 default:
412 return "???";
413 }
414}

416HeapSnapshot::HeapSnapshot(HeapProfiler* profiler,
417 v8::HeapProfiler::HeapSnapshotMode snapshot_mode,
418 v8::HeapProfiler::NumericsMode numerics_mode)
419 : profiler_(profiler),
420 snapshot_mode_(snapshot_mode),
421 numerics_mode_(numerics_mode) {
422 // It is very important to keep objects that form a heap snapshot
423 // as small as possible. Check assumptions about data structure sizes.
424 static_assert(kSystemPointerSize != 4 || sizeof(HeapGraphEdge) == 12);
425 static_assert(kSystemPointerSize != 8 || sizeof(HeapGraphEdge) == 24);
426 static_assert(kSystemPointerSize != 4 || sizeof(HeapEntry) == 32);
427#if V8_CC_MSVC
428 static_assert(kSystemPointerSize != 8 || sizeof(HeapEntry) == 48);
429#else // !V8_CC_MSVC
430 static_assert(kSystemPointerSize != 8 || sizeof(HeapEntry) == 40);
431#endif // !V8_CC_MSVC
432 memset(&gc_subroot_entries_, 0, sizeof(gc_subroot_entries_));
433}
434
435void HeapSnapshot::Delete() { profiler_->RemoveSnapshot(this); }

438 max_snapshot_js_object_id_ = profiler_->heap_object_map()->last_assigned_id();
439}

441void HeapSnapshot::AddSyntheticRootEntries() {
442 AddRootEntry();
443 AddGcRootsEntry();
444 SnapshotObjectId id = HeapObjectsMap::kGcRootsFirstSubrootId;
445 for (int root = 0; root < static_cast<int>(Root::kNumberOfRoots); root++) {
446 AddGcSubrootEntry(static_cast<Root>(root), id);
447 id += HeapObjectsMap::kObjectIdStep;
448 }
449 DCHECK_EQ(HeapObjectsMap::kFirstAvailableObjectId, id);
450}
451
452void HeapSnapshot::AddRootEntry() {
453 DCHECK_NULL(root_entry_);
454 DCHECK(entries_.empty()); // Root entry must be the first one.
455 root_entry_ = AddEntry(HeapEntry::kSynthetic, "",
456 HeapObjectsMap::kInternalRootObjectId, 0, 0);
457 DCHECK_EQ(1u, entries_.size());
458 DCHECK_EQ(root_entry_, &entries_.front());
459}
460
461void HeapSnapshot::AddGcRootsEntry() {
462 DCHECK_NULL(gc_roots_entry_);
463 gc_roots_entry_ = AddEntry(HeapEntry::kSynthetic, "(GC roots)",
464 HeapObjectsMap::kGcRootsObjectId, 0, 0);
465}

467void HeapSnapshot::AddGcSubrootEntry(Root root, SnapshotObjectId id) {
468 DCHECK_NULL(gc_subroot_entries_[static_cast<int>(root)]);
469 gc_subroot_entries_[static_cast<int>(root)] =
470 AddEntry(HeapEntry::kSynthetic, RootVisitor::RootName(root), id, 0, 0);
471}

498void HeapSnapshot::FillChildren() {
499 DCHECK(children().empty());
500 int children_index = 0;
501 for (HeapEntry& entry : entries()) {
502 children_index = entry.set_children_index(children_index);
503 }
504 DCHECK_EQ(edges().size(), static_cast<size_t>(children_index));
505 children().resize(edges().size());
506 for (HeapGraphEdge& edge : edges()) {
507 edge.from()->add_child(&edge);
508 }
509}

511HeapEntry* HeapSnapshot::GetEntryById(SnapshotObjectId id) {
512 if (entries_by_id_cache_.empty()) {
513 CHECK(is_complete());
514 entries_by_id_cache_.reserve(entries_.size());
515 for (HeapEntry& entry : entries_) {
516 entries_by_id_cache_.emplace(entry.id(), &entry);
517 }
518 }
519 auto it = entries_by_id_cache_.find(id);
520 return it != entries_by_id_cache_.end() ? it->second : nullptr;
521}

525// We split IDs on evens for embedder objects (see
526// HeapObjectsMap::GenerateId) and odds for native objects.
527const SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::kInternalRootObjectId = 1;
528const SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::kGcRootsObjectId =
529 HeapObjectsMap::kInternalRootObjectId + HeapObjectsMap::kObjectIdStep;
530const SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::kGcRootsFirstSubrootId =
531 HeapObjectsMap::kGcRootsObjectId + HeapObjectsMap::kObjectIdStep;
532const SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::kFirstAvailableObjectId =
533 HeapObjectsMap::kGcRootsFirstSubrootId +
534 static_cast<int>(Root::kNumberOfRoots) * HeapObjectsMap::kObjectIdStep;
535const SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::kFirstAvailableNativeId = 2;
536
537HeapObjectsMap::HeapObjectsMap(Heap* heap)
538 : next_id_(kFirstAvailableObjectId),
539 next_native_id_(kFirstAvailableNativeId),
540 heap_(heap) {
541 // The dummy element at zero index is needed as entries_map_ cannot hold
542 // an entry with zero value. Otherwise it's impossible to tell if
543 // LookupOrInsert has added a new item or just returning exisiting one
544 // having the value of zero.
545 entries_.emplace_back(0, kNullAddress, 0, true);
546}
547
548bool HeapObjectsMap::MoveObject(Address from, Address to, int object_size) {
549 DCHECK_NE(kNullAddress, to);
550 DCHECK_NE(kNullAddress, from);
551 if (from == to) return false;
552 void* from_value = entries_map_.Remove(reinterpret_cast<void*>(from),
553 ComputeAddressHash(from));
554 if (from_value == nullptr) {
555 // It may occur that some untracked object moves to an address X and there
556 // is a tracked object at that address. In this case we should remove the
557 // entry as we know that the object has died.
558 void* to_value = entries_map_.Remove(reinterpret_cast<void*>(to),
559 ComputeAddressHash(to));
560 if (to_value != nullptr) {
561 int to_entry_info_index =
562 static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(to_value));
563 entries_.at(to_entry_info_index).addr = kNullAddress;
564 }
565 } else {
566 base::HashMap::Entry* to_entry = entries_map_.LookupOrInsert(
567 reinterpret_cast<void*>(to), ComputeAddressHash(to));
568 if (to_entry->value != nullptr) {
569 // We found the existing entry with to address for an old object.
570 // Without this operation we will have two EntryInfo's with the same
571 // value in addr field. It is bad because later at RemoveDeadEntries
572 // one of this entry will be removed with the corresponding entries_map_
573 // entry.
574 int to_entry_info_index =
575 static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(to_entry->value));
576 entries_.at(to_entry_info_index).addr = kNullAddress;
577 }
578 int from_entry_info_index =
579 static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(from_value));
580 entries_.at(from_entry_info_index).addr = to;
581 // Size of an object can change during its life, so to keep information
582 // about the object in entries_ consistent, we have to adjust size when the
583 // object is migrated.
584 if (v8_flags.heap_profiler_trace_objects) {
585 PrintF("Move object from %p to %p old size %6d new size %6d\n",
586 reinterpret_cast<void*>(from), reinterpret_cast<void*>(to),
587 entries_.at(from_entry_info_index).size, object_size);
588 }
589 entries_.at(from_entry_info_index).size = object_size;
590 to_entry->value = from_value;
591 }
592 return from_value != nullptr;
593}
594
595void HeapObjectsMap::UpdateObjectSize(Address addr, int size) {
596 FindOrAddEntry(addr, size, MarkEntryAccessed::kNo);
597}
598
599SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::FindEntry(Address addr) {
600 base::HashMap::Entry* entry = entries_map_.Lookup(
601 reinterpret_cast<void*>(addr), ComputeAddressHash(addr));
602 if (entry == nullptr) return v8::HeapProfiler::kUnknownObjectId;
603 int entry_index = static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(entry->value));
604 EntryInfo& entry_info = entries_.at(entry_index);
605 DCHECK(static_cast<uint32_t>(entries_.size()) > entries_map_.occupancy());
606 return entry_info.id;
607}
608
609SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::FindOrAddEntry(
610 Address addr, unsigned int size, MarkEntryAccessed accessed,
611 IsNativeObject is_native_object) {
612 bool accessed_bool = accessed == MarkEntryAccessed::kYes;
613 bool is_native_object_bool = is_native_object == IsNativeObject::kYes;
614 DCHECK(static_cast<uint32_t>(entries_.size()) > entries_map_.occupancy());
615 base::HashMap::Entry* entry = entries_map_.LookupOrInsert(
616 reinterpret_cast<void*>(addr), ComputeAddressHash(addr));
617 if (entry->value != nullptr) {
618 int entry_index =
619 static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(entry->value));
620 EntryInfo& entry_info = entries_.at(entry_index);
621 entry_info.accessed = accessed_bool;
622 if (v8_flags.heap_profiler_trace_objects) {
623 PrintF("Update object size : %p with old size %d and new size %d\n",
624 reinterpret_cast<void*>(addr), entry_info.size, size);
625 }
626 entry_info.size = size;
627 DCHECK_EQ(is_native_object_bool, entry_info.id % 2 == 0);
628 return entry_info.id;
629 }
630 entry->value = reinterpret_cast<void*>(entries_.size());
631 SnapshotObjectId id =
632 is_native_object_bool ? get_next_native_id() : get_next_id();
633 entries_.push_back(EntryInfo(id, addr, size, accessed_bool));
634 DCHECK(static_cast<uint32_t>(entries_.size()) > entries_map_.occupancy());
635 return id;
636}
637
638SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::FindMergedNativeEntry(NativeObject addr) {
639 auto it = merged_native_entries_map_.find(addr);
640 if (it == merged_native_entries_map_.end())
641 return v8::HeapProfiler::kUnknownObjectId;
642 return entries_[it->second].id;
643}
644
645void HeapObjectsMap::AddMergedNativeEntry(NativeObject addr,
646 Address canonical_addr) {
647 base::HashMap::Entry* entry =
648 entries_map_.Lookup(reinterpret_cast<void*>(canonical_addr),
649 ComputeAddressHash(canonical_addr));
650 auto result = merged_native_entries_map_.insert(
651 {addr, reinterpret_cast<size_t>(entry->value)});
652 if (!result.second) {
653 result.first->second = reinterpret_cast<size_t>(entry->value);
654 }
655}
656
657void HeapObjectsMap::StopHeapObjectsTracking() { time_intervals_.clear(); }
658
659void HeapObjectsMap::UpdateHeapObjectsMap() {
660 if (v8_flags.heap_profiler_trace_objects) {
661 PrintF("Begin HeapObjectsMap::UpdateHeapObjectsMap. map has %d entries.\n",
662 entries_map_.occupancy());
663 }
664 heap_->PreciseCollectAllGarbage(GCFlag::kNoFlags,
665 GarbageCollectionReason::kHeapProfiler);
666 PtrComprCageBase cage_base(heap_->isolate());
667 CombinedHeapObjectIterator iterator(heap_);
668 for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj = iterator.Next(); !obj.is_null();
669 obj = iterator.Next()) {
670 int object_size = obj->Size(cage_base);
671 FindOrAddEntry(obj.address(), object_size);
672 if (v8_flags.heap_profiler_trace_objects) {
673 PrintF("Update object : %p %6d. Next address is %p\n",
674 reinterpret_cast<void*>(obj.address()), object_size,
675 reinterpret_cast<void*>(obj.address() + object_size));
676 }
677 }
678 RemoveDeadEntries();
679 if (v8_flags.heap_profiler_trace_objects) {
680 PrintF("End HeapObjectsMap::UpdateHeapObjectsMap. map has %d entries.\n",
681 entries_map_.occupancy());
682 }
683}
684
685SnapshotObjectId HeapObjectsMap::PushHeapObjectsStats(OutputStream* stream,
686 int64_t* timestamp_us) {
687 UpdateHeapObjectsMap();
688 time_intervals_.emplace_back(next_id_);
689 int prefered_chunk_size = stream->GetChunkSize();
690 std::vector<v8::HeapStatsUpdate> stats_buffer;
691 DCHECK(!entries_.empty());
692 EntryInfo* entry_info = &entries_.front();
693 EntryInfo* end_entry_info = &entries_.back() + 1;
694 for (size_t time_interval_index = 0;
695 time_interval_index < time_intervals_.size(); ++time_interval_index) {
696 TimeInterval& time_interval = time_intervals_[time_interval_index];
697 SnapshotObjectId time_interval_id = time_interval.id;
698 uint32_t entries_size = 0;
699 EntryInfo* start_entry_info = entry_info;
700 while (entry_info < end_entry_info && entry_info->id < time_interval_id) {
701 entries_size += entry_info->size;
702 ++entry_info;
703 }
704 uint32_t entries_count =
705 static_cast<uint32_t>(entry_info - start_entry_info);
706 if (time_interval.count != entries_count ||
707 time_interval.size != entries_size) {
708 stats_buffer.emplace_back(static_cast<uint32_t>(time_interval_index),
709 time_interval.count = entries_count,
710 time_interval.size = entries_size);
711 if (static_cast<int>(stats_buffer.size()) >= prefered_chunk_size) {
712 OutputStream::WriteResult result = stream->WriteHeapStatsChunk(
713 &stats_buffer.front(), static_cast<int>(stats_buffer.size()));
714 if (result == OutputStream::kAbort) return last_assigned_id();
715 stats_buffer.clear();
716 }
717 }
718 }
719 DCHECK(entry_info == end_entry_info);
720 if (!stats_buffer.empty()) {
721 OutputStream::WriteResult result = stream->WriteHeapStatsChunk(
722 &stats_buffer.front(), static_cast<int>(stats_buffer.size()));
723 if (result == OutputStream::kAbort) return last_assigned_id();
724 }
725 stream->EndOfStream();
726 if (timestamp_us) {
727 *timestamp_us =
728 (time_intervals_.back().timestamp - time_intervals_.front().timestamp)
729 .InMicroseconds();
730 }
731 return last_assigned_id();
732}
733
734void HeapObjectsMap::RemoveDeadEntries() {
735 DCHECK(entries_.size() > 0 && entries_.at(0).id == 0 &&
736 entries_.at(0).addr == kNullAddress);
737
738 // Build up temporary reverse map.
739 std::unordered_map<size_t, NativeObject> reverse_merged_native_entries_map;
740 for (const auto& it : merged_native_entries_map_) {
741 auto result =
742 reverse_merged_native_entries_map.emplace(it.second, it.first);
743 DCHECK(result.second);
744 USE(result);
745 }
746
747 size_t first_free_entry = 1;
748 for (size_t i = 1; i < entries_.size(); ++i) {
749 EntryInfo& entry_info = entries_.at(i);
750 auto merged_reverse_it = reverse_merged_native_entries_map.find(i);
751 if (entry_info.accessed) {
752 if (first_free_entry != i) {
753 entries_.at(first_free_entry) = entry_info;
754 }
755 entries_.at(first_free_entry).accessed = false;
756 base::HashMap::Entry* entry =
757 entries_map_.Lookup(reinterpret_cast<void*>(entry_info.addr),
758 ComputeAddressHash(entry_info.addr));
759 DCHECK(entry);
760 entry->value = reinterpret_cast<void*>(first_free_entry);
761 if (merged_reverse_it != reverse_merged_native_entries_map.end()) {
762 auto it = merged_native_entries_map_.find(merged_reverse_it->second);
763 DCHECK_NE(merged_native_entries_map_.end(), it);
764 it->second = first_free_entry;
765 }
766 ++first_free_entry;
767 } else {
768 if (entry_info.addr) {
769 entries_map_.Remove(reinterpret_cast<void*>(entry_info.addr),
770 ComputeAddressHash(entry_info.addr));
771 if (merged_reverse_it != reverse_merged_native_entries_map.end()) {
772 merged_native_entries_map_.erase(merged_reverse_it->second);
773 }
774 }
775 }
776 }
777 entries_.erase(entries_.begin() + first_free_entry, entries_.end());
778
779 DCHECK(static_cast<uint32_t>(entries_.size()) - 1 ==
780 entries_map_.occupancy());
781}

809Tagged<JSFunction> V8HeapExplorer::GetLocationFunction(
810 Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
811 DisallowHeapAllocation no_gc;
812
813 if (IsJSFunction(object)) {
814 return Cast<JSFunction>(object);
815 } else if (IsJSGeneratorObject(object)) {
816 Tagged<JSGeneratorObject> gen = Cast<JSGeneratorObject>(object);
817 return gen->function();
818 } else if (IsJSObject(object)) {
819 Tagged<JSObject> obj = Cast<JSObject>(object);
820 Tagged<JSFunction> maybe_constructor =
821 GetConstructor(heap_->isolate(), obj);
822
823 return maybe_constructor;
824 }
825
826 return JSFunction();
827}

830 Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
831 DisallowHeapAllocation no_gc;
832 Tagged<JSFunction> func = GetLocationFunction(object);
833 if (!func.is_null()) {
834 ExtractLocationForJSFunction(entry, func);
835 }

837
838void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractLocationForJSFunction(HeapEntry* entry,
839 Tagged<JSFunction> func) {
840 if (!IsScript(func->shared()->script())) return;
841 Tagged<Script> script = Cast<Script>(func->shared()->script());
842 int scriptId = script->id();
843 int start = func->shared()->StartPosition();
844 Script::PositionInfo info;
845 if (script->has_line_ends()) {
846 script->GetPositionInfo(start, &info);
847 } else {
848 script->GetPositionInfoWithLineEnds(
849 start, &info, snapshot_->GetScriptLineEnds(script->id()));
850 }
851 snapshot_->AddLocation(entry, scriptId, info.line, info.column);
852}
853
854HeapEntry* V8HeapExplorer::AddEntry(Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
855 PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate());
856 InstanceType instance_type = object->map(cage_base)->instance_type();
857 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSObject(instance_type)) {
858 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSFunction(instance_type)) {
859 Tagged<JSFunction> func = Cast<JSFunction>(object);
860 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared = func->shared();
861 const char* name = names_->GetName(shared->Name());
862 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kClosure, name);
863
864 } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSBoundFunction(instance_type)) {
865 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kClosure, "native_bind");
866 }
867 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSRegExp(instance_type)) {
868 Tagged<JSRegExp> re = Cast<JSRegExp>(object);
869 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kRegExp,
870 names_->GetName(re->source()));
871 }
872 // TODO(v8:12674) Fix and run full gcmole.
873 DisableGCMole no_gcmole;
874 const char* name = names_->GetName(
875 GetConstructorName(heap_->isolate(), Cast<JSObject>(object)));
876 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSGlobalObject(instance_type)) {
877 auto it = global_object_tag_map_.find(Cast<JSGlobalObject>(object));
878 if (it != global_object_tag_map_.end()) {
879 name = names_->GetFormatted("%s / %s", name, it->second);
880 }
881 }
882 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kObject, name);
883
884 } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsString(instance_type)) {
885 Tagged<String> string = Cast<String>(object);
886 if (IsConsString(string, cage_base)) {
887 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kConsString, "(concatenated string)");
888 } else if (IsSlicedString(string, cage_base)) {
889 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kSlicedString, "(sliced string)");
890 } else {
891 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kString,
892 names_->GetName(Cast<String>(object)));
893 }
894 } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsSymbol(instance_type)) {
895 if (Cast<Symbol>(object)->is_private())
896 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kHidden, "private symbol");
897 else
898 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kSymbol, "symbol");
899
900 } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsBigInt(instance_type)) {
901 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kBigInt, "bigint");
902
903 } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsInstructionStream(instance_type) ||
904 InstanceTypeChecker::IsCode(instance_type)) {
905 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kCode, "");
906
907 } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsSharedFunctionInfo(instance_type)) {
908 Tagged<String> name = Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(object)->Name();
909 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kCode, names_->GetName(name));
910
911 } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsScript(instance_type)) {
912 Tagged<Object> name = Cast<Script>(object)->name();
913 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kCode,
914 IsString(name) ? names_->GetName(Cast<String>(name)) : "");
915
916 } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsNativeContext(instance_type)) {
917 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kHidden, "system / NativeContext");
918
919 } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsContext(instance_type)) {
920 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kObject, "system / Context");
921
922 } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsHeapNumber(instance_type)) {
923 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kHeapNumber, "heap number");
924 }
925#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
926 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsWasmObject(instance_type)) {
927 Tagged<WasmTypeInfo> info = object->map()->wasm_type_info();
928 // Getting the trusted data is safe; structs and arrays always have their
929 // trusted data defined.
930 wasm::NamesProvider* names =
931 info->trusted_data(isolate())->native_module()->GetNamesProvider();
932 wasm::StringBuilder sb;
933 names->PrintTypeName(sb, info->type_index());
934 sb << " (wasm)" << '\0';
935 const char* name = names_->GetCopy(sb.start());
936 return AddEntry(object, HeapEntry::kObject, name);
937 }
938 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsWasmNull(instance_type)) {
939 // Inlined copies of {GetSystemEntryType}, {GetSystemEntryName}, and
940 // {AddEntry}, allowing us to override the size.
941 // The actual object's size is fairly large (at the time of this writing,
942 // just over 64 KB) and mostly includes a guard region. We report it as
943 // much smaller to avoid confusion.
944 static constexpr size_t kSize = WasmNull::kHeaderSize;
945 return AddEntry(object.address(), HeapEntry::kHidden, "system / WasmNull",
946 kSize);
947 }
948#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
949
950 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsForeign(instance_type)) {
951 Tagged<Foreign> foreign = Cast<Foreign>(object);
952 ExternalPointerTag tag = foreign->GetTag();
953
954 size_t size = object->Size();
955 const char* name = nullptr;
956 // TODO(saelo): consider creating a global mapping of ExternalPointerTags
957 // for Managed objects to their name if we need this anywhere else.
958 switch (tag) {
959 case kGenericManagedTag:
960 name = "system / Managed<Unknown>";
961 break;
962#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
963 case kWasmWasmStreamingTag:
964 name = "system / Managed<WasmStreaming>";
965 break;
966 case kWasmFuncDataTag:
967 name = "system / Managed<wasm::FuncData>";
968 break;
969 case kWasmManagedDataTag:
970 name = "system / Managed<wasm::ManagedData>";
971 break;
972 case kWasmNativeModuleTag:
973 size = Cast<Managed<wasm::NativeModule>>(foreign)
974 ->raw()
975 ->EstimateCurrentMemoryConsumption();
976 name = "system / Managed<wasm::NativeModule>";
977 break;
978#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
979 case kIcuBreakIteratorTag:
980 name = "system / Managed<icu::BreakIterator>";
981 break;
982 case kIcuUnicodeStringTag:
983 name = "system / Managed<icu::UnicodeString>";
984 break;
985 case kIcuListFormatterTag:
986 name = "system / Managed<icu::ListFormatter>";
987 break;
988 case kIcuLocaleTag:
989 name = "system / Managed<icu::Locale>";
990 break;
991 case kIcuSimpleDateFormatTag:
992 name = "system / Managed<icu::SimpleDateFormat>";
993 break;
994 case kIcuDateIntervalFormatTag:
995 name = "system / Managed<icu::DateIntervalFormat>";
996 break;
997 case kIcuRelativeDateTimeFormatterTag:
998 name = "system / Managed<icu::RelativeDateTimeFormatter>";
999 break;
1000 case kIcuLocalizedNumberFormatterTag:
1001 name = "system / Managed<icu::LocalizedNumberFormatter>";
1002 break;
1003 case kIcuPluralRulesTag:
1004 name = "system / Managed<icu::PluralRules>";
1005 break;
1006 case kIcuCollatorTag:
1007 name = "system / Managed<icu::Collator>";
1008 break;
1009 case kDisplayNamesInternalTag:
1010 name = "system / Managed<DisplayNamesInternal>";
1011 break;
1012 default:
1013 DCHECK(!kAnyManagedExternalPointerTagRange.Contains(tag));
1014 }
1015 if (name != nullptr) {
1016 return AddEntry(object.address(), HeapEntry::kHidden, name, size);
1017 }
1018 }
1019
1020 return AddEntry(object, GetSystemEntryType(object),
1021 GetSystemEntryName(object));
1022}
1023
1024HeapEntry* V8HeapExplorer::AddEntry(Tagged<HeapObject> object,
1025 HeapEntry::Type type, const char* name) {
1026 PtrComprCageBase cage_base(isolate());
1027 return AddEntry(object.address(), type, name, object->Size(cage_base));
1028}
1029
1030HeapEntry* V8HeapExplorer::AddEntry(Address address, HeapEntry::Type type,
1031 const char* name, size_t size) {
1032 if (v8_flags.heap_profiler_show_hidden_objects &&
1033 type == HeapEntry::kHidden) {
1034 type = HeapEntry::kNative;
1035 }
1036 SnapshotObjectId object_id = heap_object_map_->FindOrAddEntry(
1037 address, static_cast<unsigned int>(size));
1038 unsigned trace_node_id = 0;
1039 if (AllocationTracker* allocation_tracker =
1040 snapshot_->profiler()->allocation_tracker()) {
1041 trace_node_id =
1042 allocation_tracker->address_to_trace()->GetTraceNodeId(address);
1043 }
1044 return snapshot_->AddEntry(type, name, object_id, size, trace_node_id);
1045}
1046
1047const char* V8HeapExplorer::GetSystemEntryName(Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
1048 if (IsMap(object)) {
1049 switch (Cast<Map>(object)->instance_type()) {
1050#define MAKE_STRING_MAP_CASE(instance_type, size, name, Name) \
1051 case instance_type: \
1052 return "system / Map (" #Name ")";
1053 STRING_TYPE_LIST(MAKE_STRING_MAP_CASE)
1054#undef MAKE_STRING_MAP_CASE
1055 default:
1056 return "system / Map";
1057 }
1058 }
1059
1060 InstanceType type = object->map()->instance_type();
1061
1062 // Empty string names are special: TagObject can overwrite them, and devtools
1063 // will report them as "(internal array)".
1064 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsFixedArray(type) ||
1065 InstanceTypeChecker::IsFixedDoubleArray(type) ||
1066 InstanceTypeChecker::IsByteArray(type)) {
1067 return "";
1068 }
1069
1070 switch (type) {
1071#define MAKE_TORQUE_CASE(Name, TYPE) \
1072 case TYPE: \
1073 return "system / " #Name;
1074 // The following lists include every non-String instance type.
1075 // This includes a few types that already have non-"system" names assigned
1076 // by AddEntry, but this is a convenient way to avoid manual upkeep here.
1077 TORQUE_INSTANCE_CHECKERS_SINGLE_FULLY_DEFINED(MAKE_TORQUE_CASE)
1078 TORQUE_INSTANCE_CHECKERS_MULTIPLE_FULLY_DEFINED(MAKE_TORQUE_CASE)
1079 TORQUE_INSTANCE_CHECKERS_SINGLE_ONLY_DECLARED(MAKE_TORQUE_CASE)
1080 TORQUE_INSTANCE_CHECKERS_MULTIPLE_ONLY_DECLARED(MAKE_TORQUE_CASE)
1081#undef MAKE_TORQUE_CASE
1082
1083 // Strings were already handled by AddEntry.
1084#define MAKE_STRING_CASE(instance_type, size, name, Name) \
1085 case instance_type: \
1086 UNREACHABLE();
1087 STRING_TYPE_LIST(MAKE_STRING_CASE)
1088#undef MAKE_STRING_CASE
1089 }
1090}
1091
1092HeapEntry::Type V8HeapExplorer::GetSystemEntryType(Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
1093 InstanceType type = object->map()->instance_type();
1094 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsAllocationSite(type) ||
1095 InstanceTypeChecker::IsArrayBoilerplateDescription(type) ||
1096 InstanceTypeChecker::IsBytecodeArray(type) ||
1097 InstanceTypeChecker::IsBytecodeWrapper(type) ||
1098 InstanceTypeChecker::IsClosureFeedbackCellArray(type) ||
1099 InstanceTypeChecker::IsCode(type) ||
1100 InstanceTypeChecker::IsCodeWrapper(type) ||
1101 InstanceTypeChecker::IsFeedbackCell(type) ||
1102 InstanceTypeChecker::IsFeedbackMetadata(type) ||
1103 InstanceTypeChecker::IsFeedbackVector(type) ||
1104 InstanceTypeChecker::IsInstructionStream(type) ||
1105 InstanceTypeChecker::IsInterpreterData(type) ||
1106 InstanceTypeChecker::IsLoadHandler(type) ||
1107 InstanceTypeChecker::IsObjectBoilerplateDescription(type) ||
1108 InstanceTypeChecker::IsPreparseData(type) ||
1109 InstanceTypeChecker::IsRegExpBoilerplateDescription(type) ||
1110 InstanceTypeChecker::IsScopeInfo(type) ||
1111 InstanceTypeChecker::IsStoreHandler(type) ||
1112 InstanceTypeChecker::IsTemplateObjectDescription(type) ||
1113 InstanceTypeChecker::IsTurbofanType(type) ||
1114 InstanceTypeChecker::IsUncompiledData(type)) {
1115 return HeapEntry::kCode;
1116 }
1117
1118 // This check must come second, because some subtypes of FixedArray are
1119 // determined above to represent code content.
1120 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsFixedArray(type) ||
1121 InstanceTypeChecker::IsFixedDoubleArray(type) ||
1122 InstanceTypeChecker::IsByteArray(type)) {
1123 return HeapEntry::kArray;
1124 }
1125
1126 // Maps in read-only space are for internal V8 data, not user-defined object
1127 // shapes.
1128 if ((InstanceTypeChecker::IsMap(type) &&
1129 !MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(object)->InReadOnlySpace()) ||
1130 InstanceTypeChecker::IsDescriptorArray(type) ||
1131 InstanceTypeChecker::IsTransitionArray(type) ||
1132 InstanceTypeChecker::IsPrototypeInfo(type) ||
1133 InstanceTypeChecker::IsEnumCache(type)) {
1134 return HeapEntry::kObjectShape;
1135 }
1136
1137 return HeapEntry::kHidden;
1138}
1139
1140void V8HeapExplorer::PopulateLineEnds() {
1141 std::vector<Handle<Script>> scripts;
1142 HandleScope scope(isolate());
1143
1144 {
1145 Script::Iterator iterator(isolate());
1146 for (Tagged<Script> script = iterator.Next(); !script.is_null();
1147 script = iterator.Next()) {
1148 if (!script->has_line_ends()) {
1149 scripts.push_back(handle(script, isolate()));
1150 }
1151 }
1152 }
1153
1154 for (auto& script : scripts) {
1155 snapshot_->AddScriptLineEnds(script->id(),
1156 Script::GetLineEnds(isolate(), script));
1157 }
1158}
1159
1160uint32_t V8HeapExplorer::EstimateObjectsCount() {
1161 CombinedHeapObjectIterator it(heap_, HeapObjectIterator::kNoFiltering);
1162 uint32_t objects_count = 0;
1163 // Avoid overflowing the objects count. In worst case, we will show the same
1164 // progress for a longer period of time, but we do not expect to have that
1165 // many objects.
1166 while (!it.Next().is_null() &&
1167 objects_count != std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max())
1168 ++objects_count;
1169 return objects_count;
1170}

1172#ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
1173namespace {
1174int AdjustEmbedderFieldIndex(Tagged<HeapObject> heap_obj, int field_index) {
1175 Tagged<Map> map = heap_obj->map();
1176 if (JSObject::MayHaveEmbedderFields(map)) {
1177 int emb_start_index = (JSObject::GetEmbedderFieldsStartOffset(map) +
1178 EmbedderDataSlot::kTaggedPayloadOffset) /
1179 kTaggedSize;
1180 int emb_field_count = JSObject::GetEmbedderFieldCount(map);
1181 int emb_end_index = emb_start_index + emb_field_count;
1182 if (base::IsInRange(field_index, emb_start_index, emb_end_index)) {
1183 return -EmbedderDataSlot::kTaggedPayloadOffset / kTaggedSize;
1184 }
1185 }
1186 return 0;
1187}
1188} // namespace
1189#endif // V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
1190class IndexedReferencesExtractor : public ObjectVisitorWithCageBases {
1191 public:
1192 IndexedReferencesExtractor(V8HeapExplorer* generator,
1193 Tagged<HeapObject> parent_obj, HeapEntry* parent)
1194 : ObjectVisitorWithCageBases(generator->isolate()),
1195 generator_(generator),
1196 parent_obj_(parent_obj),
1197 parent_start_(parent_obj_->RawMaybeWeakField(0)),
1198 parent_end_(
1199 parent_obj_->RawMaybeWeakField(parent_obj_->Size(cage_base()))),
1200 parent_(parent),
1201 next_index_(0) {}
1202 void VisitPointers(Tagged<HeapObject> host, ObjectSlot start,
1203 ObjectSlot end) override {
1204 VisitPointers(host, MaybeObjectSlot(start), MaybeObjectSlot(end));
1205 }
1206 void VisitMapPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> object) override {
1207 VisitSlotImpl(cage_base(), object->map_slot());
1208 }
1209 void VisitPointers(Tagged<HeapObject> host, MaybeObjectSlot start,
1210 MaybeObjectSlot end) override {
1211 // [start,end) must be a sub-region of [parent_start_, parent_end), i.e.
1212 // all the slots must point inside the object.
1213 CHECK_LE(parent_start_, start);
1214 CHECK_LE(end, parent_end_);
1215 for (MaybeObjectSlot slot = start; slot < end; ++slot) {
1216 VisitSlotImpl(cage_base(), slot);
1217 }
1218 }
1219
1220 void VisitInstructionStreamPointer(Tagged<Code> host,
1221 InstructionStreamSlot slot) override {
1222 VisitSlotImpl(code_cage_base(), slot);
1223 }
1224
1225 void VisitCodeTarget(Tagged<InstructionStream> host,
1226 RelocInfo* rinfo) override {
1227 Tagged<InstructionStream> target =
1228 InstructionStream::FromTargetAddress(rinfo->target_address());
1229 VisitHeapObjectImpl(target, -1);
1230 }
1231
1232 void VisitEmbeddedPointer(Tagged<InstructionStream> host,
1233 RelocInfo* rinfo) override {
1234 Tagged<HeapObject> object = rinfo->target_object(cage_base());
1235 Tagged<Code> code = UncheckedCast<Code>(host->raw_code(kAcquireLoad));
1236 if (code->IsWeakObject(object)) {
1237 generator_->SetWeakReference(parent_, next_index_++, object, {});
1238 } else {
1239 VisitHeapObjectImpl(object, -1);
1240 }
1241 }
1242
1243 void VisitIndirectPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> host, IndirectPointerSlot slot,
1244 IndirectPointerMode mode) override {
1245 VisitSlotImpl(generator_->isolate(), slot);
1246 }
1247
1248 void VisitProtectedPointer(Tagged<TrustedObject> host,
1249 ProtectedPointerSlot slot) override {
1250 // TODO(saelo): the cage base doesn't currently matter as it isn't used,
1251 // but technically we should either use the trusted cage base here or
1252 // remove the cage_base parameter.
1253 const PtrComprCageBase unused_cage_base(kNullAddress);
1254 VisitSlotImpl(unused_cage_base, slot);
1255 }
1256
1257 void VisitProtectedPointer(Tagged<TrustedObject> host,
1258 ProtectedMaybeObjectSlot slot) override {
1259 // TODO(saelo): the cage base doesn't currently matter as it isn't used,
1260 // but technically we should either use the trusted cage base here or
1261 // remove the cage_base parameter.
1262 const PtrComprCageBase unused_cage_base(kNullAddress);
1263 VisitSlotImpl(unused_cage_base, slot);
1264 }
1265
1266 void VisitJSDispatchTableEntry(Tagged<HeapObject> host,
1267 JSDispatchHandle handle) override {
1268#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1269 // TODO(saelo): implement proper support for these fields here, similar to
1270 // how we handle indirect pointer or protected pointer fields.
1271 // Currently we only expect to see FeedbackCells or JSFunctions here.
1272 if (IsJSFunction(host)) {
1273 int field_index = JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset / kTaggedSize;
1274 CHECK(generator_->visited_fields_[field_index]);
1275 generator_->visited_fields_[field_index] = false;
1276 } else if (IsCode(host) || IsFeedbackCell(host)) {
1277 // Nothing to do: the Code object is tracked as part of the JSFunction.
1278 } else {
1279 UNREACHABLE();
1280 }
1281#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1282 }
1283
1284 private:
1285 template <typename TIsolateOrCageBase, typename TSlot>
1286 V8_INLINE void VisitSlotImpl(TIsolateOrCageBase isolate_or_cage_base,
1287 TSlot slot) {
1288 int field_index =
1289 static_cast<int>(slot.address() - parent_start_.address()) /
1290 TSlot::kSlotDataSize;
1291#ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
1292 field_index += AdjustEmbedderFieldIndex(parent_obj_, field_index);
1293#endif
1294 DCHECK_GE(field_index, 0);
1295 if (generator_->visited_fields_[field_index]) {
1296 generator_->visited_fields_[field_index] = false;
1297 } else {
1298 Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
1299 auto loaded_value = slot.load(isolate_or_cage_base);
1300 if (loaded_value.GetHeapObjectIfStrong(&heap_object)) {
1301 VisitHeapObjectImpl(heap_object, field_index);
1302 } else if (loaded_value.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&heap_object)) {
1303 generator_->SetWeakReference(parent_, next_index_++, heap_object, {});
1304 }
1305 }
1306 }
1307
1308 V8_INLINE void VisitHeapObjectImpl(Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object,
1309 int field_index) {
1310 DCHECK_LE(-1, field_index);
1311 // The last parameter {field_offset} is only used to check some well-known
1312 // skipped references, so passing -1 * kTaggedSize for objects embedded
1313 // into code is fine.
1314 generator_->SetHiddenReference(parent_obj_, parent_, next_index_++,
1315 heap_object, field_index * kTaggedSize);
1316 }
1317
1318 V8HeapExplorer* generator_;
1319 Tagged<HeapObject> parent_obj_;
1320 MaybeObjectSlot parent_start_;
1321 MaybeObjectSlot parent_end_;
1322 HeapEntry* parent_;
1323 int next_index_;
1324};

1326void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractReferences(HeapEntry* entry,
1327 Tagged<HeapObject> obj) {
1328 if (IsJSGlobalProxy(obj)) {
1329 ExtractJSGlobalProxyReferences(entry, Cast<JSGlobalProxy>(obj));
1330 } else if (IsJSArrayBuffer(obj)) {
1331 ExtractJSArrayBufferReferences(entry, Cast<JSArrayBuffer>(obj));
1332 } else if (IsJSObject(obj)) {
1333 if (IsJSWeakSet(obj)) {
1334 ExtractJSWeakCollectionReferences(entry, Cast<JSWeakSet>(obj));
1335 } else if (IsJSWeakMap(obj)) {
1336 ExtractJSWeakCollectionReferences(entry, Cast<JSWeakMap>(obj));
1337 } else if (IsJSSet(obj)) {
1338 ExtractJSCollectionReferences(entry, Cast<JSSet>(obj));
1339 } else if (IsJSMap(obj)) {
1340 ExtractJSCollectionReferences(entry, Cast<JSMap>(obj));
1341 } else if (IsJSPromise(obj)) {
1342 ExtractJSPromiseReferences(entry, Cast<JSPromise>(obj));
1343 } else if (IsJSGeneratorObject(obj)) {
1344 ExtractJSGeneratorObjectReferences(entry, Cast<JSGeneratorObject>(obj));
1345 } else if (IsJSWeakRef(obj)) {
1346 ExtractJSWeakRefReferences(entry, Cast<JSWeakRef>(obj));
1347#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1348 } else if (IsWasmInstanceObject(obj)) {
1349 ExtractWasmInstanceObjectReferences(Cast<WasmInstanceObject>(obj), entry);
1350 } else if (IsWasmModuleObject(obj)) {
1351 ExtractWasmModuleObjectReferences(Cast<WasmModuleObject>(obj), entry);
1352#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1353 }
1354 ExtractJSObjectReferences(entry, Cast<JSObject>(obj));
1355 } else if (IsString(obj)) {
1356 ExtractStringReferences(entry, Cast<String>(obj));
1357 } else if (IsSymbol(obj)) {
1358 ExtractSymbolReferences(entry, Cast<Symbol>(obj));
1359 } else if (IsMap(obj)) {
1360 ExtractMapReferences(entry, Cast<Map>(obj));
1361 } else if (IsSharedFunctionInfo(obj)) {
1362 ExtractSharedFunctionInfoReferences(entry, Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(obj));
1363 } else if (IsScript(obj)) {
1364 ExtractScriptReferences(entry, Cast<Script>(obj));
1365 } else if (IsAccessorInfo(obj)) {
1366 ExtractAccessorInfoReferences(entry, Cast<AccessorInfo>(obj));
1367 } else if (IsAccessorPair(obj)) {
1368 ExtractAccessorPairReferences(entry, Cast<AccessorPair>(obj));
1369 } else if (IsCode(obj)) {
1370 ExtractCodeReferences(entry, Cast<Code>(obj));
1371 } else if (IsInstructionStream(obj)) {
1372 ExtractInstructionStreamReferences(entry, Cast<InstructionStream>(obj));
1373 } else if (IsCell(obj)) {
1374 ExtractCellReferences(entry, Cast<Cell>(obj));
1375 } else if (IsFeedbackCell(obj)) {
1376 ExtractFeedbackCellReferences(entry, Cast<FeedbackCell>(obj));
1377 } else if (IsPropertyCell(obj)) {
1378 ExtractPropertyCellReferences(entry, Cast<PropertyCell>(obj));
1379 } else if (IsPrototypeInfo(obj)) {
1380 ExtractPrototypeInfoReferences(entry, Cast<PrototypeInfo>(obj));
1381 } else if (IsAllocationSite(obj)) {
1382 ExtractAllocationSiteReferences(entry, Cast<AllocationSite>(obj));
1383 } else if (IsArrayBoilerplateDescription(obj)) {
1384 ExtractArrayBoilerplateDescriptionReferences(
1385 entry, Cast<ArrayBoilerplateDescription>(obj));
1386 } else if (IsRegExpBoilerplateDescription(obj)) {
1387 ExtractRegExpBoilerplateDescriptionReferences(
1388 entry, Cast<RegExpBoilerplateDescription>(obj));
1389 } else if (IsFeedbackVector(obj)) {
1390 ExtractFeedbackVectorReferences(entry, Cast<FeedbackVector>(obj));
1391 } else if (IsDescriptorArray(obj)) {
1392 ExtractDescriptorArrayReferences(entry, Cast<DescriptorArray>(obj));
1393 } else if (IsEnumCache(obj)) {
1394 ExtractEnumCacheReferences(entry, Cast<EnumCache>(obj));
1395 } else if (IsTransitionArray(obj)) {
1396 ExtractTransitionArrayReferences(entry, Cast<TransitionArray>(obj));
1397 } else if (IsWeakFixedArray(obj)) {
1398 ExtractWeakArrayReferences(OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(WeakFixedArray), entry,
1399 Cast<WeakFixedArray>(obj));
1400 } else if (IsWeakArrayList(obj)) {
1401 ExtractWeakArrayReferences(WeakArrayList::kHeaderSize, entry,
1402 Cast<WeakArrayList>(obj));
1403 } else if (IsContext(obj)) {
1404 ExtractContextReferences(entry, Cast<Context>(obj));
1405 } else if (IsEphemeronHashTable(obj)) {
1406 ExtractEphemeronHashTableReferences(entry, Cast<EphemeronHashTable>(obj));
1407 } else if (IsFixedArray(obj)) {
1408 ExtractFixedArrayReferences(entry, Cast<FixedArray>(obj));
1409 } else if (IsWeakCell(obj)) {
1410 ExtractWeakCellReferences(entry, Cast<WeakCell>(obj));
1411 } else if (IsHeapNumber(obj)) {
1412 if (snapshot_->capture_numeric_value()) {
1413 ExtractNumberReference(entry, obj);
1414 }
1415 } else if (IsBytecodeArray(obj)) {
1416 ExtractBytecodeArrayReferences(entry, Cast<BytecodeArray>(obj));
1417 } else if (IsScopeInfo(obj)) {
1418 ExtractScopeInfoReferences(entry, Cast<ScopeInfo>(obj));
1419#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1420 } else if (IsWasmStruct(obj)) {
1421 ExtractWasmStructReferences(Cast<WasmStruct>(obj), entry);
1422 } else if (IsWasmArray(obj)) {
1423 ExtractWasmArrayReferences(Cast<WasmArray>(obj), entry);
1424 } else if (IsWasmTrustedInstanceData(obj)) {
1425 ExtractWasmTrustedInstanceDataReferences(Cast<WasmTrustedInstanceData>(obj),
1426 entry);
1427#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1428 }
1429}

1433
1434void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractJSObjectReferences(HeapEntry* entry,
1435 Tagged<JSObject> js_obj) {
1436 Tagged<HeapObject> obj = js_obj;
1437 ExtractPropertyReferences(js_obj, entry);
1438 ExtractElementReferences(js_obj, entry);
1439 ExtractInternalReferences(js_obj, entry);
1440 Isolate* isolate = Isolate::FromHeap(heap_);
1441 PrototypeIterator iter(isolate, js_obj);
1442 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
1443 SetPropertyReference(entry, roots.proto_string(), iter.GetCurrent());
1444 if (IsJSBoundFunction(obj)) {
1445 Tagged<JSBoundFunction> js_fun = Cast<JSBoundFunction>(obj);
1446 TagObject(js_fun->bound_arguments(), "(bound arguments)");
1447 SetInternalReference(entry, "bindings", js_fun->bound_arguments(),
1448 JSBoundFunction::kBoundArgumentsOffset);
1449 SetInternalReference(entry, "bound_this", js_fun->bound_this(),
1450 JSBoundFunction::kBoundThisOffset);
1451 SetInternalReference(entry, "bound_function",
1452 js_fun->bound_target_function(),
1453 JSBoundFunction::kBoundTargetFunctionOffset);
1454 Tagged<FixedArray> bindings = js_fun->bound_arguments();
1455 for (int i = 0; i < bindings->length(); i++) {
1456 const char* reference_name = names_->GetFormatted("bound_argument_%d", i);
1457 SetNativeBindReference(entry, reference_name, bindings->get(i));
1458 }
1459 } else if (IsJSFunction(obj)) {
1460 Tagged<JSFunction> js_fun = Cast<JSFunction>(js_obj);
1461 if (js_fun->has_prototype_slot()) {
1462 Tagged<Object> proto_or_map =
1463 js_fun->prototype_or_initial_map(kAcquireLoad);
1464 if (!IsTheHole(proto_or_map, isolate)) {
1465 if (!IsMap(proto_or_map)) {
1466 SetPropertyReference(entry, roots.prototype_string(), proto_or_map,
1467 nullptr,
1468 JSFunction::kPrototypeOrInitialMapOffset);
1469 } else {
1470 SetPropertyReference(entry, roots.prototype_string(),
1471 js_fun->prototype());
1472 SetInternalReference(entry, "initial_map", proto_or_map,
1473 JSFunction::kPrototypeOrInitialMapOffset);
1474 }
1475 }
1476 }
1477 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info = js_fun->shared();
1478 TagObject(js_fun->raw_feedback_cell(), "(function feedback cell)");
1479 SetInternalReference(entry, "feedback_cell", js_fun->raw_feedback_cell(),
1480 JSFunction::kFeedbackCellOffset);
1481 TagObject(shared_info, "(shared function info)");
1482 SetInternalReference(entry, "shared", shared_info,
1483 JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset);
1484 TagObject(js_fun->context(), "(context)");
1485 SetInternalReference(entry, "context", js_fun->context(),
1486 JSFunction::kContextOffset);
1487#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1488 SetInternalReference(entry, "code", js_fun->code(isolate),
1489 JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset);
1490#else
1491 SetInternalReference(entry, "code", js_fun->code(isolate),
1492 JSFunction::kCodeOffset);
1493#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1494 } else if (IsJSGlobalObject(obj)) {
1495 Tagged<JSGlobalObject> global_obj = Cast<JSGlobalObject>(obj);
1496 SetInternalReference(entry, "global_proxy", global_obj->global_proxy(),
1497 JSGlobalObject::kGlobalProxyOffset);
1498 } else if (IsJSArrayBufferView(obj)) {
1499 Tagged<JSArrayBufferView> view = Cast<JSArrayBufferView>(obj);
1500 SetInternalReference(entry, "buffer", view->buffer(),
1501 JSArrayBufferView::kBufferOffset);
1502 }
1503
1504 TagObject(js_obj->raw_properties_or_hash(), "(object properties)");
1505 SetInternalReference(entry, "properties", js_obj->raw_properties_or_hash(),
1506 JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset);
1507
1508 TagObject(js_obj->elements(), "(object elements)");
1509 SetInternalReference(entry, "elements", js_obj->elements(),
1510 JSObject::kElementsOffset);
1511}

1513void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractStringReferences(HeapEntry* entry,
1514 Tagged<String> string) {
1515 if (IsConsString(string)) {
1516 Tagged<ConsString> cs = Cast<ConsString>(string);
1517 SetInternalReference(entry, "first", cs->first(),
1518 offsetof(ConsString, first_));
1519 SetInternalReference(entry, "second", cs->second(),
1520 offsetof(ConsString, second_));
1521 } else if (IsSlicedString(string)) {
1522 Tagged<SlicedString> ss = Cast<SlicedString>(string);
1523 SetInternalReference(entry, "parent", ss->parent(),
1524 offsetof(SlicedString, parent_));
1525 } else if (IsThinString(string)) {
1526 Tagged<ThinString> ts = Cast<ThinString>(string);
1527 SetInternalReference(entry, "actual", ts->actual(),
1528 offsetof(ThinString, actual_));
1529 }
1530}

1532void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractSymbolReferences(HeapEntry* entry,
1533 Tagged<Symbol> symbol) {
1534 SetInternalReference(entry, "name", symbol->description(),
1535 offsetof(Symbol, description_));
1536}

1540 SetInternalReference(entry, "table", collection->table(),
1541 JSCollection::kTableOffset);

1544void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractJSWeakCollectionReferences(

1547 JSWeakCollection::kTableOffset);
1548}
1549
1550void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractEphemeronHashTableReferences(
1551 HeapEntry* entry, Tagged<EphemeronHashTable> table) {
1552 for (InternalIndex i : table->IterateEntries()) {
1553 int key_index = EphemeronHashTable::EntryToIndex(i) +
1554 EphemeronHashTable::kEntryKeyIndex;
1555 int value_index = EphemeronHashTable::EntryToValueIndex(i);
1556 Tagged<Object> key = table->get(key_index);
1557 Tagged<Object> value = table->get(value_index);
1558 SetWeakReference(entry, key_index, key,
1559 table->OffsetOfElementAt(key_index));
1560 SetWeakReference(entry, value_index, value,
1561 table->OffsetOfElementAt(value_index));
1562 HeapEntry* key_entry = GetEntry(key);
1563 HeapEntry* value_entry = GetEntry(value);
1564 HeapEntry* table_entry = GetEntry(table);
1565 if (key_entry && value_entry && !IsUndefined(key)) {
1566 const char* edge_name = names_->GetFormatted(
1567 "part of key (%s @%u) -> value (%s @%u) pair in WeakMap (table @%u)",
1568 key_entry->name(), key_entry->id(), value_entry->name(),
1569 value_entry->id(), table_entry->id());
1570 key_entry->SetNamedAutoIndexReference(HeapGraphEdge::kInternal, edge_name,
1571 value_entry, names_, generator_,
1572 HeapEntry::kEphemeron);
1573 table_entry->SetNamedAutoIndexReference(
1574 HeapGraphEdge::kInternal, edge_name, value_entry, names_, generator_,
1575 HeapEntry::kEphemeron);
1576 }
1577 }
1578}
1579
1580// These static arrays are used to prevent excessive code-size in
1581// ExtractContextReferences below, which would happen if we called
1582// SetInternalReference for every native context field in a macro.
1583static const struct {
1584 int index;
1585 const char* name;
1586} native_context_names[] = {
1587#define CONTEXT_FIELD_INDEX_NAME(index, _, name) {Context::index, #name},
1588 NATIVE_CONTEXT_FIELDS(CONTEXT_FIELD_INDEX_NAME)
1589#undef CONTEXT_FIELD_INDEX_NAME
1590};
1591
1592void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractContextReferences(HeapEntry* entry,
1593 Tagged<Context> context) {
1594 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1595 if (!IsNativeContext(context) && context->is_declaration_context()) {
1596 Tagged<ScopeInfo> scope_info = context->scope_info();
1597 // Add context allocated locals.
1598 for (auto it : ScopeInfo::IterateLocalNames(scope_info, no_gc)) {
1599 int idx = scope_info->ContextHeaderLength() + it->index();
1600 SetContextReference(entry, it->name(), context->get(idx),
1601 Context::OffsetOfElementAt(idx));
1602 }
1603 if (scope_info->HasContextAllocatedFunctionName()) {
1604 Tagged<String> name = Cast<String>(scope_info->FunctionName());
1605 int idx = scope_info->FunctionContextSlotIndex(name);
1606 if (idx >= 0) {
1607 SetContextReference(entry, name, context->get(idx),
1608 Context::OffsetOfElementAt(idx));
1609 }
1610 }
1611 }
1612
1613 SetInternalReference(
1614 entry, "scope_info", context->get(Context::SCOPE_INFO_INDEX),
1615 FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::SCOPE_INFO_INDEX));
1616 SetInternalReference(entry, "previous", context->get(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX),
1617 FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::PREVIOUS_INDEX));
1618 if (context->has_extension()) {
1619 SetInternalReference(
1620 entry, "extension", context->get(Context::EXTENSION_INDEX),
1621 FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::EXTENSION_INDEX));
1622 }
1623
1624 if (IsNativeContext(context)) {
1625 TagObject(context->normalized_map_cache(), "(context norm. map cache)");
1626 TagObject(context->embedder_data(), "(context data)");
1627 for (size_t i = 0; i < arraysize(native_context_names); i++) {
1628 int index = native_context_names[i].index;
1629 const char* name = native_context_names[i].name;
1630 SetInternalReference(entry, name, context->get(index),
1631 FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(index));
1632 }
1633
1634 static_assert(Context::NEXT_CONTEXT_LINK == Context::FIRST_WEAK_SLOT);
1635 static_assert(Context::FIRST_WEAK_SLOT + 1 ==
1636 Context::NATIVE_CONTEXT_SLOTS);
1637 }
1638}
1639
1640void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractMapReferences(HeapEntry* entry, Tagged<Map> map) {
1641 Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_raw_transitions_or_prototype_info =
1642 map->raw_transitions();
1643 Tagged<HeapObject> raw_transitions_or_prototype_info;
1644 if (maybe_raw_transitions_or_prototype_info.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(
1645 &raw_transitions_or_prototype_info)) {
1646 DCHECK(IsMap(raw_transitions_or_prototype_info));
1647 SetWeakReference(entry, "transition", raw_transitions_or_prototype_info,
1648 Map::kTransitionsOrPrototypeInfoOffset);
1649 } else if (maybe_raw_transitions_or_prototype_info.GetHeapObjectIfStrong(
1650 &raw_transitions_or_prototype_info)) {
1651 if (IsTransitionArray(raw_transitions_or_prototype_info)) {
1652 Tagged<TransitionArray> transitions =
1653 Cast<TransitionArray>(raw_transitions_or_prototype_info);
1654 if (map->CanTransition() && transitions->HasPrototypeTransitions()) {
1655 TagObject(transitions->GetPrototypeTransitions(),
1656 "(prototype transitions)");
1657 }
1658 TagObject(transitions, "(transition array)");
1659 SetInternalReference(entry, "transitions", transitions,
1660 Map::kTransitionsOrPrototypeInfoOffset);
1661 } else if (IsFixedArray(raw_transitions_or_prototype_info)) {
1662 TagObject(raw_transitions_or_prototype_info, "(transition)");
1663 SetInternalReference(entry, "transition",
1664 raw_transitions_or_prototype_info,
1665 Map::kTransitionsOrPrototypeInfoOffset);
1666 } else if (map->is_prototype_map()) {
1667 TagObject(raw_transitions_or_prototype_info, "prototype_info");
1668 SetInternalReference(entry, "prototype_info",
1669 raw_transitions_or_prototype_info,
1670 Map::kTransitionsOrPrototypeInfoOffset);
1671 }
1672 }
1673 Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors = map->instance_descriptors();
1674 TagObject(descriptors, "(map descriptors)");
1675 SetInternalReference(entry, "descriptors", descriptors,
1676 Map::kInstanceDescriptorsOffset);
1677 SetInternalReference(entry, "prototype", map->prototype(),
1678 Map::kPrototypeOffset);
1679 if (IsContextMap(map) || IsMapMap(map)) {
1680 Tagged<Object> native_context = map->native_context_or_null();
1681 TagObject(native_context, "(native context)");
1682 SetInternalReference(entry, "native_context", native_context,
1683 Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset);
1684 } else {
1685 Tagged<Object> constructor_or_back_pointer =
1686 map->constructor_or_back_pointer();
1687 if (IsMap(constructor_or_back_pointer)) {
1688 TagObject(constructor_or_back_pointer, "(back pointer)");
1689 SetInternalReference(entry, "back_pointer", constructor_or_back_pointer,
1690 Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset);
1691 } else if (IsFunctionTemplateInfo(constructor_or_back_pointer)) {
1692 TagObject(constructor_or_back_pointer, "(constructor function data)");
1693 SetInternalReference(entry, "constructor_function_data",
1694 constructor_or_back_pointer,
1695 Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset);
1696 } else {
1697 SetInternalReference(entry, "constructor", constructor_or_back_pointer,
1698 Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset);
1699 }
1700 }
1701 TagObject(map->dependent_code(), "(dependent code)");
1702 SetInternalReference(entry, "dependent_code", map->dependent_code(),
1703 Map::kDependentCodeOffset);
1704 TagObject(map->prototype_validity_cell(kRelaxedLoad),
1705 "(prototype validity cell)", HeapEntry::kObjectShape);
1706}
1707
1708void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractSharedFunctionInfoReferences(
1709 HeapEntry* entry, Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> shared) {
1710 TagObject(shared, "(shared function info)");
1711 {
1712 std::unique_ptr<char[]> name = shared->DebugNameCStr();
1713 Tagged<Code> code = shared->GetCode(isolate());
1714 TagObject(code, name[0] != '\0'
1715 ? names_->GetFormatted("(code for %s)", name.get())
1716 : names_->GetFormatted("(%s code)",
1717 CodeKindToString(code->kind())));
1718 if (code->has_instruction_stream()) {
1719 TagObject(
1720 code->instruction_stream(),
1721 name[0] != '\0'
1722 ? names_->GetFormatted("(instruction stream for %s)", name.get())
1723 : names_->GetFormatted("(%s instruction stream)",
1724 CodeKindToString(code->kind())));
1725 }
1726 }
1727
1728 Tagged<Object> name_or_scope_info = shared->name_or_scope_info(kAcquireLoad);
1729 if (IsScopeInfo(name_or_scope_info)) {
1730 TagObject(name_or_scope_info, "(function scope info)");
1731 }
1732 SetInternalReference(entry, "name_or_scope_info", name_or_scope_info,
1733 SharedFunctionInfo::kNameOrScopeInfoOffset);
1734 SetInternalReference(entry, "script", shared->script(kAcquireLoad),
1735 SharedFunctionInfo::kScriptOffset);
1736 SetInternalReference(entry, "trusted_function_data",

1743 entry, "raw_outer_scope_info_or_feedback_metadata",

1815void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractCodeReferences(HeapEntry* entry,
1816 Tagged<Code> code) {
1817 if (!code->has_instruction_stream()) return;
1818
1819 SetInternalReference(entry, "instruction_stream", code->instruction_stream(),
1820 Code::kInstructionStreamOffset);
1821
1822 if (code->kind() == CodeKind::BASELINE) {
1823 TagObject(code->bytecode_or_interpreter_data(), "(interpreter data)");
1824 SetInternalReference(entry, "interpreter_data",
1825 code->bytecode_or_interpreter_data(),
1826 Code::kDeoptimizationDataOrInterpreterDataOffset);
1827 TagObject(code->bytecode_offset_table(), "(bytecode offset table)",
1828 HeapEntry::kCode);
1829 SetInternalReference(entry, "bytecode_offset_table",
1830 code->bytecode_offset_table(),
1831 Code::kPositionTableOffset);
1832 } else if (code->uses_deoptimization_data()) {
1833 Tagged<DeoptimizationData> deoptimization_data =
1834 Cast<DeoptimizationData>(code->deoptimization_data());
1835 TagObject(deoptimization_data, "(code deopt data)", HeapEntry::kCode);
1836 SetInternalReference(entry, "deoptimization_data", deoptimization_data,
1837 Code::kDeoptimizationDataOrInterpreterDataOffset);
1838 if (deoptimization_data->length() > 0) {
1839 TagObject(deoptimization_data->FrameTranslation(), "(code deopt data)",
1840 HeapEntry::kCode);
1841 TagObject(deoptimization_data->LiteralArray(), "(code deopt data)",
1842 HeapEntry::kCode);
1843 TagObject(deoptimization_data->InliningPositions(), "(code deopt data)",
1844 HeapEntry::kCode);
1845 }
1846 TagObject(code->source_position_table(), "(source position table)",
1847 HeapEntry::kCode);
1848 SetInternalReference(entry, "source_position_table",
1849 code->source_position_table(),
1850 Code::kPositionTableOffset);
1851 }
1852}

1981void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractNumberReference(HeapEntry* entry,
1982 Tagged<Object> number) {
1983 DCHECK(IsNumber(number));
1984
1985 // Must be large enough to fit any double, int, or size_t.
1986 char arr[32];
1987 base::Vector<char> buffer = base::ArrayVector(arr);
1988
1989 std::string_view string;
1990 if (IsSmi(number)) {
1991 int int_value = Smi::ToInt(number);
1992 string = IntToStringView(int_value, buffer);
1993 } else {
1994 double double_value = Cast<HeapNumber>(number)->value();
1995 string = DoubleToStringView(double_value, buffer);
1996 }
1997
1998 // GetCopy() requires a null-terminated C-String, as the underlying hash map
1999 // uses strcmp.
2000 const char* name = names_->GetCopy(std::string(string).c_str());
2001
2002 SnapshotObjectId id = heap_object_map_->get_next_id();
2003 HeapEntry* child_entry =
2004 snapshot_->AddEntry(HeapEntry::kString, name, id, 0, 0);
2005 entry->SetNamedReference(HeapGraphEdge::kInternal, "value", child_entry,
2006 generator_);
2007}

2014 TagObject(bytecode->raw_source_position_table(kAcquireLoad),
2015 "(source position table)", HeapEntry::kCode);
2016}

2026void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractFeedbackVectorReferences(
2027 HeapEntry* entry, Tagged<FeedbackVector> feedback_vector) {
2028#ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2029 Tagged<MaybeObject> code = feedback_vector->maybe_optimized_code();
2030 Tagged<HeapObject> code_heap_object;
2031 if (code.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&code_heap_object)) {
2032 SetWeakReference(entry, "optimized code", code_heap_object,
2033 FeedbackVector::kMaybeOptimizedCodeOffset);
2034 }
2035#endif // !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2036 for (int i = 0; i < feedback_vector->length(); ++i) {
2037 Tagged<MaybeObject> maybe_entry = *(feedback_vector->slots_start() + i);
2038 Tagged<HeapObject> entry;
2039 if (maybe_entry.GetHeapObjectIfStrong(&entry) &&
2040 (entry->map(isolate())->instance_type() == WEAK_FIXED_ARRAY_TYPE ||
2041 IsFixedArrayExact(entry))) {
2042 TagObject(entry, "(feedback)", HeapEntry::kCode);
2043 }
2044 }

2047void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractDescriptorArrayReferences(
2048 HeapEntry* entry, Tagged<DescriptorArray> array) {
2049 SetInternalReference(entry, "enum_cache", array->enum_cache(),
2050 DescriptorArray::kEnumCacheOffset);
2051 MaybeObjectSlot start = MaybeObjectSlot(array->GetDescriptorSlot(0));
2052 MaybeObjectSlot end = MaybeObjectSlot(
2053 array->GetDescriptorSlot(array->number_of_all_descriptors()));
2054 for (int i = 0; start + i < end; ++i) {
2055 MaybeObjectSlot slot = start + i;
2056 int offset = static_cast<int>(slot.address() - array.address());
2057 Tagged<MaybeObject> object = *slot;
2058 Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
2059 if (object.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&heap_object)) {
2060 SetWeakReference(entry, i, heap_object, offset);
2061 } else if (object.GetHeapObjectIfStrong(&heap_object)) {
2062 SetInternalReference(entry, i, heap_object, offset);
2063 }
2064 }
2065}

2081template <typename T>
2082void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractWeakArrayReferences(int header_size,
2083 HeapEntry* entry,
2084 Tagged<T> array) {
2085 for (int i = 0; i < array->length(); ++i) {
2086 Tagged<MaybeObject> object = array->get(i);
2087 Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
2088 if (object.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&heap_object)) {
2089 SetWeakReference(entry, i, heap_object, header_size + i * kTaggedSize);
2090 } else if (object.GetHeapObjectIfStrong(&heap_object)) {
2091 SetInternalReference(entry, i, heap_object,
2092 header_size + i * kTaggedSize);
2093 }
2094 }
2095}
2096
2097void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractPropertyReferences(Tagged<JSObject> js_obj,
2098 HeapEntry* entry) {
2099 Isolate* isolate = js_obj->GetIsolate();
2100 if (js_obj->HasFastProperties()) {
2101 Tagged<DescriptorArray> descs =
2102 js_obj->map()->instance_descriptors(isolate);
2103 for (InternalIndex i : js_obj->map()->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
2104 PropertyDetails details = descs->GetDetails(i);
2105 switch (details.location()) {
2106 case PropertyLocation::kField: {
2107 if (!snapshot_->capture_numeric_value()) {
2108 Representation r = details.representation();
2109 if (r.IsSmi() || r.IsDouble()) break;
2110 }
2111
2112 Tagged<Name> k = descs->GetKey(i);
2113 FieldIndex field_index =
2114 FieldIndex::ForDetails(js_obj->map(), details);
2115 Tagged<Object> value = js_obj->RawFastPropertyAt(field_index);
2116 int field_offset =
2117 field_index.is_inobject() ? field_index.offset() : -1;
2118
2119 SetDataOrAccessorPropertyReference(details.kind(), entry, k, value,
2120 nullptr, field_offset);
2121 break;
2122 }
2123 case PropertyLocation::kDescriptor:
2124 SetDataOrAccessorPropertyReference(details.kind(), entry,
2125 descs->GetKey(i),
2126 descs->GetStrongValue(i));
2127 break;
2128 }
2129 }
2130 } else if (IsJSGlobalObject(js_obj)) {
2131 // We assume that global objects can only have slow properties.
2132 Tagged<GlobalDictionary> dictionary =
2133 Cast<JSGlobalObject>(js_obj)->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad);
2134 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
2135 for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
2136 if (!dictionary->IsKey(roots, dictionary->KeyAt(i))) continue;
2137 Tagged<PropertyCell> cell = dictionary->CellAt(i);
2138 Tagged<Name> name = cell->name();
2139 Tagged<Object> value = cell->value();
2140 PropertyDetails details = cell->property_details();
2141 SetDataOrAccessorPropertyReference(details.kind(), entry, name, value);
2142 }
2143 } else if (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
2144 // SwissNameDictionary::IterateEntries creates a Handle, which should not
2145 // leak out of here.
2146 HandleScope scope(isolate);
2147
2148 Tagged<SwissNameDictionary> dictionary =
2149 js_obj->property_dictionary_swiss();
2150 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
2151 for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
2152 Tagged<Object> k = dictionary->KeyAt(i);
2153 if (!dictionary->IsKey(roots, k)) continue;
2154 Tagged<Object> value = dictionary->ValueAt(i);
2155 PropertyDetails details = dictionary->DetailsAt(i);
2156 SetDataOrAccessorPropertyReference(details.kind(), entry, Cast<Name>(k),
2157 value);
2158 }
2159 } else {
2160 Tagged<NameDictionary> dictionary = js_obj->property_dictionary();
2161 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
2162 for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
2163 Tagged<Object> k = dictionary->KeyAt(i);
2164 if (!dictionary->IsKey(roots, k)) continue;
2165 Tagged<Object> value = dictionary->ValueAt(i);
2166 PropertyDetails details = dictionary->DetailsAt(i);
2167 SetDataOrAccessorPropertyReference(details.kind(), entry, Cast<Name>(k),
2168 value);
2169 }
2170 }
2171}
2172
2173void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractAccessorPairProperty(HeapEntry* entry,
2174 Tagged<Name> key,
2175 Tagged<Object> callback_obj,
2176 int field_offset) {
2177 if (!IsAccessorPair(callback_obj)) return;
2178 Tagged<AccessorPair> accessors = Cast<AccessorPair>(callback_obj);
2179 SetPropertyReference(entry, key, accessors, nullptr, field_offset);
2180 Tagged<Object> getter = accessors->getter();
2181 if (!IsOddball(getter)) {
2182 SetPropertyReference(entry, key, getter, "get %s");
2183 }
2184 Tagged<Object> setter = accessors->setter();
2185 if (!IsOddball(setter)) {
2186 SetPropertyReference(entry, key, setter, "set %s");
2187 }
2188}
2189
2190void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractElementReferences(Tagged<JSObject> js_obj,
2191 HeapEntry* entry) {
2192 ReadOnlyRoots roots = GetReadOnlyRoots();
2193 if (js_obj->HasObjectElements()) {
2194 Tagged<FixedArray> elements = Cast<FixedArray>(js_obj->elements());
2195 int length = IsJSArray(js_obj) ? Smi::ToInt(Cast<JSArray>(js_obj)->length())
2196 : elements->length();
2197 for (int i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
2198 if (!IsTheHole(elements->get(i), roots)) {
2199 SetElementReference(entry, i, elements->get(i));
2200 }
2201 }
2202 } else if (js_obj->HasDictionaryElements()) {
2203 Tagged<NumberDictionary> dictionary = js_obj->element_dictionary();
2204 for (InternalIndex i : dictionary->IterateEntries()) {
2205 Tagged<Object> k = dictionary->KeyAt(i);
2206 if (!dictionary->IsKey(roots, k)) continue;
2207 uint32_t index =
2208 static_cast<uint32_t>(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(k)));
2209 SetElementReference(entry, index, dictionary->ValueAt(i));
2210 }
2211 }
2212}
