2214void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractInternalReferences(Tagged<JSObject> js_obj,
2215 HeapEntry* entry) {
2216 int length = js_obj->GetEmbedderFieldCount();
2217 for (int i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
2218 Tagged<Object> o = js_obj->GetEmbedderField(i);
2219 SetInternalReference(entry, i, o, js_obj->GetEmbedderFieldOffset(i));
2220 }
2221}
2222
2223#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2224
2225void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractWasmStructReferences(Tagged<WasmStruct> obj,
2226 HeapEntry* entry) {
2227 wasm::StructType* type = obj->type();
2228 Tagged<WasmTypeInfo> info = obj->map()->wasm_type_info();
2229 // Getting the trusted data is safe; structs always have their trusted data
2230 // defined.
2231 wasm::NamesProvider* names =
2232 info->trusted_data(isolate())->native_module()->GetNamesProvider();
2233 Isolate* isolate = heap_->isolate();
2234 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < type->field_count(); i++) {
2235 wasm::StringBuilder sb;
2236 names->PrintFieldName(sb, info->module_type_index(), i);
2237 sb << '\0';
2238 const char* field_name = names_->GetCopy(sb.start());
2239 switch (type->field(i).kind()) {
2240 case wasm::kI8:
2241 case wasm::kI16:
2242 case wasm::kI32:
2243 case wasm::kI64:
2244 case wasm::kF16:
2245 case wasm::kF32:
2246 case wasm::kF64:
2247 case wasm::kS128: {
2248 if (!snapshot_->capture_numeric_value()) continue;
2249 std::string value_string = obj->GetFieldValue(i).to_string();
2250 const char* value_name = names_->GetCopy(value_string.c_str());
2251 SnapshotObjectId id = heap_object_map_->get_next_id();
2252 HeapEntry* child_entry =
2253 snapshot_->AddEntry(HeapEntry::kString, value_name, id, 0, 0);
2254 entry->SetNamedReference(HeapGraphEdge::kInternal, field_name,
2255 child_entry, generator_);
2256 break;
2257 }
2258 case wasm::kRef:
2259 case wasm::kRefNull: {
2260 int field_offset = type->field_offset(i);
2261 Tagged<Object> value = obj->RawField(field_offset).load(isolate);
2262 // We could consider hiding {null} fields by default (like we do for
2263 // arrays, see below), but for now we always include them, in the hope
2264 // that they might help identify opportunities for struct size
2265 // reductions.
2266 HeapEntry* value_entry = GetEntry(value);
2267 entry->SetNamedReference(HeapGraphEdge::kProperty, field_name,
2268 value_entry, generator_);
2269 MarkVisitedField(WasmStruct::kHeaderSize + field_offset);
2270 break;
2271 }
2272 case wasm::kRtt:
2273 case wasm::kVoid:
2274 case wasm::kTop:
2275 case wasm::kBottom:
2276 UNREACHABLE();
2277 }
2278 }
2279}
2280
2281void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractWasmArrayReferences(Tagged<WasmArray> obj,
2282 HeapEntry* entry) {
2283 if (!obj->type()->element_type().is_reference()) return;
2284 Isolate* isolate = heap_->isolate();
2285 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
2286 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < obj->length(); i++) {
2287 Tagged<Object> value = obj->ElementSlot(i).load(isolate);
2288 // By default, don't show {null} entries, to reduce noise: they can make
2289 // it difficult to find non-null entries in sparse arrays. We piggyback
2290 // on the "capture numeric values" flag as an opt-in to produce more
2291 // detailed/verbose snapshots, including {null} entries.
2292 if (value != roots.wasm_null() || snapshot_->capture_numeric_value()) {
2293 SetElementReference(entry, i, value);
2294 }
2295 MarkVisitedField(obj->element_offset(i));
2296 }
2297}
2298
2299void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractWasmTrustedInstanceDataReferences(
2300 Tagged<WasmTrustedInstanceData> trusted_data, HeapEntry* entry) {
2301 PtrComprCageBase cage_base(heap_->isolate());
2302 for (size_t i = 0; i < WasmTrustedInstanceData::kTaggedFieldOffsets.size();
2303 i++) {
2304 const uint16_t offset = WasmTrustedInstanceData::kTaggedFieldOffsets[i];
2305 SetInternalReference(
2306 entry, WasmTrustedInstanceData::kTaggedFieldNames[i],
2307 TaggedField<Object>::load(cage_base, trusted_data, offset), offset);
2308 }
2309 for (size_t i = 0; i < WasmTrustedInstanceData::kProtectedFieldNames.size();
2310 i++) {
2311 const uint16_t offset = WasmTrustedInstanceData::kProtectedFieldOffsets[i];
2312 SetInternalReference(
2313 entry, WasmTrustedInstanceData::kProtectedFieldNames[i],
2314 trusted_data->RawProtectedPointerField(offset).load(heap_->isolate()),
2315 offset);
2316 }
2317}
2318
2319#define ASSERT_FIRST_FIELD(Class, Field) \
2320 static_assert(Class::Super::kHeaderSize == Class::k##Field##Offset)
2321#define ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE_FIELDS(Class, Field, NextField) \
2322 static_assert(Class::k##Field##OffsetEnd + 1 == Class::k##NextField##Offset)
2323#define ASSERT_LAST_FIELD(Class, Field) \
2324 static_assert(Class::k##Field##OffsetEnd + 1 == Class::kHeaderSize)
2325
2326void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractWasmInstanceObjectReferences(
2327 Tagged<WasmInstanceObject> instance_object, HeapEntry* entry) {
2328 // The static assertions verify that we do not miss any fields here when we
2329 // update the class definition.
2330 ASSERT_FIRST_FIELD(WasmInstanceObject, TrustedData);
2331 SetInternalReference(entry, "trusted_data",
2332 instance_object->trusted_data(heap_->isolate()),
2333 WasmInstanceObject::kTrustedDataOffset);
2334 ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE_FIELDS(WasmInstanceObject, TrustedData, ModuleObject);
2335 SetInternalReference(entry, "module_object", instance_object->module_object(),
2336 WasmInstanceObject::kModuleObjectOffset);
2337 ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE_FIELDS(WasmInstanceObject, ModuleObject, ExportsObject);
2338 SetInternalReference(entry, "exports", instance_object->exports_object(),
2339 WasmInstanceObject::kExportsObjectOffset);
2340 ASSERT_LAST_FIELD(WasmInstanceObject, ExportsObject);
2341}
2342
2343void V8HeapExplorer::ExtractWasmModuleObjectReferences(
2344 Tagged<WasmModuleObject> module_object, HeapEntry* entry) {
2345 // The static assertions verify that we do not miss any fields here when we
2346 // update the class definition.
2347 ASSERT_FIRST_FIELD(WasmModuleObject, ManagedNativeModule);
2348 SetInternalReference(entry, "managed_native_module",
2349 module_object->managed_native_module(),
2350 WasmModuleObject::kManagedNativeModuleOffset);
2351 ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE_FIELDS(WasmModuleObject, ManagedNativeModule, Script);
2352 SetInternalReference(entry, "script", module_object->script(),
2353 WasmModuleObject::kScriptOffset);
2354 ASSERT_LAST_FIELD(WasmModuleObject, Script);
2355}
2356
2357#undef ASSERT_FIRST_FIELD
2358#undef ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE_FIELDS
2359#undef ASSERT_LAST_FIELD
2360
2361#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

2363Tagged<JSFunction> V8HeapExplorer::GetConstructor(Isolate* isolate,
2364 Tagged<JSReceiver> receiver) {
2365 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2366 HandleScope scope(isolate);
2367 MaybeDirectHandle<JSFunction> maybe_constructor =
2368 JSReceiver::GetConstructor(isolate, direct_handle(receiver, isolate));
2369
2370 if (maybe_constructor.is_null()) return JSFunction();
2371
2372 return *maybe_constructor.ToHandleChecked();
2373}

2376 Tagged<JSObject> object) {

2380 direct_handle(object, isolate));

2383HeapEntry* V8HeapExplorer::GetEntry(Tagged<Object> obj) {
2384 if (IsHeapObject(obj)) {
2385 return generator_->FindOrAddEntry(reinterpret_cast<void*>(obj.ptr()), this);
2386 }
2387
2388 DCHECK(IsSmi(obj));
2389 if (!snapshot_->capture_numeric_value()) {
2390 return nullptr;
2391 }
2392 return generator_->FindOrAddEntry(Cast<Smi>(obj), this);
2393}
2394
2395class RootsReferencesExtractor : public RootVisitor {
2396 public:
2397 explicit RootsReferencesExtractor(V8HeapExplorer* explorer)
2398 : explorer_(explorer), visiting_weak_roots_(false) {}
2399
2400 void SetVisitingWeakRoots() { visiting_weak_roots_ = true; }
2401
2402 void VisitRootPointer(Root root, const char* description,
2403 FullObjectSlot p) override {
2404 Tagged<Object> object = *p;
2405#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DIRECT_HANDLE
2406 if (object.ptr() == kTaggedNullAddress) return;
2407#endif
2408 if (root == Root::kBuiltins) {
2409 explorer_->TagBuiltinCodeObject(Cast<Code>(object), description);
2410 }
2411 explorer_->SetGcSubrootReference(root, description, visiting_weak_roots_,
2412 object);
2413 }
2414
2415 void VisitRootPointers(Root root, const char* description,
2416 FullObjectSlot start, FullObjectSlot end) override {
2417 for (FullObjectSlot p = start; p < end; ++p) {
2418 DCHECK(!MapWord::IsPacked(p.Relaxed_Load().ptr()));
2419 VisitRootPointer(root, description, p);
2420 }
2421 }
2422
2423 void VisitRootPointers(Root root, const char* description,
2424 OffHeapObjectSlot start,
2425 OffHeapObjectSlot end) override {
2426 DCHECK_EQ(root, Root::kStringTable);
2427 PtrComprCageBase cage_base(explorer_->heap_->isolate());
2428 for (OffHeapObjectSlot p = start; p < end; ++p) {
2429 explorer_->SetGcSubrootReference(root, description, visiting_weak_roots_,
2430 p.load(cage_base));
2431 }
2432 }
2433
2434 // Keep this synced with
2435 // MarkCompactCollector::RootMarkingVisitor::VisitRunningCode.
2436 void VisitRunningCode(FullObjectSlot code_slot,
2437 FullObjectSlot istream_or_smi_zero_slot) final {
2438 Tagged<Object> istream_or_smi_zero = *istream_or_smi_zero_slot;
2439 if (istream_or_smi_zero != Smi::zero()) {
2440 Tagged<Code> code = Cast<Code>(*code_slot);
2441 code->IterateDeoptimizationLiterals(this);
2442 VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, istream_or_smi_zero_slot);
2443 }
2444 VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr, code_slot);
2445 }
2446
2447 private:
2448 V8HeapExplorer* explorer_;
2449 bool visiting_weak_roots_;
2450};
2451
2452bool V8HeapExplorer::IterateAndExtractReferences(
2453 HeapSnapshotGenerator* generator) {
2454 generator_ = generator;
2455
2456 // Create references to the synthetic roots.
2457 SetRootGcRootsReference();
2458 for (int root = 0; root < static_cast<int>(Root::kNumberOfRoots); root++) {
2459 SetGcRootsReference(static_cast<Root>(root));
2460 }
2461
2462 // Make sure builtin code objects get their builtin tags
2463 // first. Otherwise a particular JSFunction object could set
2464 // its custom name to a generic builtin.
2465 RootsReferencesExtractor extractor(this);
2466 ReadOnlyRoots(heap_).Iterate(&extractor);
2467 heap_->IterateRoots(
2468 &extractor,
2469 base::EnumSet<SkipRoot>{SkipRoot::kWeak, SkipRoot::kTracedHandles});
2470 // TODO(v8:11800): The heap snapshot generator incorrectly considers the weak
2471 // string tables as strong retainers. Move IterateWeakRoots after
2472 // SetVisitingWeakRoots.
2473 heap_->IterateWeakRoots(&extractor, {});
2474 extractor.SetVisitingWeakRoots();
2475 heap_->IterateWeakGlobalHandles(&extractor);
2476
2477 bool interrupted = false;
2478
2479 CombinedHeapObjectIterator iterator(heap_);
2480 PtrComprCageBase cage_base(heap_->isolate());
2481 // Heap iteration need not be finished but progress reporting may depend on
2482 // it being finished.
2483 for (Tagged<HeapObject> obj = iterator.Next(); !obj.is_null();
2484 obj = iterator.Next(), progress_->ProgressStep()) {
2485 if (interrupted) continue;
2486
2487 max_pointers_ = obj->Size(cage_base) / kTaggedSize;
2488 if (max_pointers_ > visited_fields_.size()) {
2489 // Reallocate to right size.
2490 visited_fields_.resize(max_pointers_, false);
2491 }
2492
2493#ifdef V8_ENABLE_HEAP_SNAPSHOT_VERIFY
2494 std::unique_ptr<HeapEntryVerifier> verifier;
2495 // MarkingVisitorBase doesn't expect that we will ever visit read-only
2496 // objects, and fails DCHECKs if we attempt to. Read-only objects can
2497 // never retain read-write objects, so there is no risk in skipping
2498 // verification for them.
2499 if (v8_flags.heap_snapshot_verify &&
2500 !MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(obj)->InReadOnlySpace()) {
2501 verifier = std::make_unique<HeapEntryVerifier>(generator, obj);
2502 }
2503#endif
2504
2505 HeapEntry* entry = GetEntry(obj);
2506 ExtractReferences(entry, obj);
2507 SetInternalReference(entry, "map", obj->map(cage_base),
2508 HeapObject::kMapOffset);
2509 // Extract unvisited fields as hidden references and restore tags
2510 // of visited fields.
2511 IndexedReferencesExtractor refs_extractor(this, obj, entry);
2512 VisitObject(heap_->isolate(), obj, &refs_extractor);
2513
2514#if DEBUG
2515 // Ensure visited_fields_ doesn't leak to the next object.
2516 for (size_t i = 0; i < max_pointers_; ++i) {
2517 DCHECK(!visited_fields_[i]);
2518 }
2519#endif // DEBUG
2520
2521 // Extract location for specific object types
2522 ExtractLocation(entry, obj);
2523
2524 if (!progress_->ProgressReport(false)) interrupted = true;
2525 }
2526
2527 generator_ = nullptr;
2528 return interrupted ? false : progress_->ProgressReport(true);
2529}
2530
2531bool V8HeapExplorer::IsEssentialObject(Tagged<Object> object) {
2532 if (!IsHeapObject(object)) return false;
2533 // Avoid comparing objects in other pointer compression cages to objects
2534 // inside the main cage as the comparison may only look at the lower 32 bits.
2535 if (HeapLayout::InCodeSpace(Cast<HeapObject>(object)) ||
2536 HeapLayout::InTrustedSpace(Cast<HeapObject>(object))) {
2537 return true;
2538 }
2539 Isolate* isolate = heap_->isolate();
2540 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
2541 return !IsOddball(object, isolate) && object != roots.the_hole_value() &&
2542 object != roots.empty_byte_array() &&
2543 object != roots.empty_fixed_array() &&
2544 object != roots.empty_weak_fixed_array() &&
2545 object != roots.empty_descriptor_array() &&
2546 object != roots.fixed_array_map() && object != roots.cell_map() &&
2547 object != roots.global_property_cell_map() &&
2548 object != roots.shared_function_info_map() &&
2549 object != roots.free_space_map() &&
2550 object != roots.one_pointer_filler_map() &&
2551 object != roots.two_pointer_filler_map();
2552}
2553
2554bool V8HeapExplorer::IsEssentialHiddenReference(Tagged<Object> parent,
2555 int field_offset) {
2556 if (IsAllocationSite(parent) &&
2557 field_offset == AllocationSite::kWeakNextOffset)
2558 return false;
2559 if (IsContext(parent) &&
2560 field_offset == Context::OffsetOfElementAt(Context::NEXT_CONTEXT_LINK))
2561 return false;
2562 if (IsJSFinalizationRegistry(parent) &&
2563 field_offset == JSFinalizationRegistry::kNextDirtyOffset)
2564 return false;
2565 return true;
2566}

2568void V8HeapExplorer::SetContextReference(HeapEntry* parent_entry,
2569 Tagged<String> reference_name,
2570 Tagged<Object> child_obj,
2571 int field_offset) {
2572 HeapEntry* child_entry = GetEntry(child_obj);
2573 if (child_entry == nullptr) return;
2574 parent_entry->SetNamedReference(HeapGraphEdge::kContextVariable,
2575 names_->GetName(reference_name), child_entry,
2576 generator_);
2577 MarkVisitedField(field_offset);
2578}

2580void V8HeapExplorer::MarkVisitedField(int offset) {
2581 if (offset < 0) return;
2582 int index = offset / kTaggedSize;
2583 DCHECK_LT(index, max_pointers_);
2584 DCHECK(!visited_fields_[index]);
2585 visited_fields_[index] = true;
2586}

2594 child_entry, generator_);

2633void V8HeapExplorer::SetHiddenReference(Tagged<HeapObject> parent_obj,
2634 HeapEntry* parent_entry, int index,
2635 Tagged<Object> child_obj,
2636 int field_offset) {
2637 DCHECK_EQ(parent_entry, GetEntry(parent_obj));

2640 return;

2646 child_entry, generator_);

2680void V8HeapExplorer::SetDataOrAccessorPropertyReference(
2681 PropertyKind kind, HeapEntry* parent_entry, Tagged<Name> reference_name,
2682 Tagged<Object> child_obj, const char* name_format_string,
2683 int field_offset) {
2684 if (kind == PropertyKind::kAccessor) {
2685 ExtractAccessorPairProperty(parent_entry, reference_name, child_obj,
2686 field_offset);
2687 } else {
2688 SetPropertyReference(parent_entry, reference_name, child_obj,
2689 name_format_string, field_offset);

2692
2693void V8HeapExplorer::SetPropertyReference(HeapEntry* parent_entry,
2694 Tagged<Name> reference_name,
2695 Tagged<Object> child_obj,
2696 const char* name_format_string,
2697 int field_offset) {
2698 HeapEntry* child_entry = GetEntry(child_obj);
2699 if (child_entry == nullptr) return;
2700 HeapGraphEdge::Type type =
2701 IsSymbol(reference_name) || Cast<String>(reference_name)->length() > 0
2702 ? HeapGraphEdge::kProperty
2703 : HeapGraphEdge::kInternal;
2704 const char* name = name_format_string != nullptr && IsString(reference_name)
2705 ? names_->GetFormatted(
2706 name_format_string,
2707 Cast<String>(reference_name)->ToCString().get())
2708 : names_->GetName(reference_name);
2709
2710 parent_entry->SetNamedReference(type, name, child_entry, generator_);
2711 MarkVisitedField(field_offset);
2712}

2716 HeapGraphEdge::kElement, snapshot_->gc_roots(), generator_);

2730
2731void V8HeapExplorer::SetGcSubrootReference(Root root, const char* description,
2732 bool is_weak,
2733 Tagged<Object> child_obj) {
2734 if (IsSmi(child_obj)) {
2735 // TODO(arenevier): if we handle smis here, the snapshot gets 2 to 3 times
2736 // slower on large heaps. According to perf, The bulk of the extra works
2737 // happens in TemplateHashMapImpl::Probe method, when tyring to get
2738 // names->GetFormatted("%d / %s", index, description)
2739 return;
2740 }
2741 HeapEntry* child_entry = GetEntry(child_obj);
2742 if (child_entry == nullptr) return;
2743 auto child_heap_obj = Cast<HeapObject>(child_obj);
2744 const char* name = GetStrongGcSubrootName(child_heap_obj);
2745 HeapGraphEdge::Type edge_type =
2746 is_weak ? HeapGraphEdge::kWeak : HeapGraphEdge::kInternal;
2747 if (name != nullptr) {
2748 snapshot_->gc_subroot(root)->SetNamedReference(edge_type, name, child_entry,
2749 generator_);
2750 } else {
2751 snapshot_->gc_subroot(root)->SetNamedAutoIndexReference(
2752 edge_type, description, child_entry, names_, generator_);
2753 }
2754
2755 // For full heap snapshots we do not emit user roots but rather rely on
2756 // regular GC roots to retain objects.
2757 if (snapshot_->expose_internals()) return;
2758
2759 // Add a shortcut to JS global object reference at snapshot root.
2760 // That allows the user to easily find global objects. They are
2761 // also used as starting points in distance calculations.
2762 if (is_weak || !IsNativeContext(child_heap_obj)) return;
2763
2764 Tagged<JSGlobalObject> global =
2765 Cast<Context>(child_heap_obj)->global_object();
2766 if (!IsJSGlobalObject(global)) return;
2767
2768 if (!user_roots_.insert(global).second) return;
2769
2770 SetUserGlobalReference(global);
2771}
2772
2773const char* V8HeapExplorer::GetStrongGcSubrootName(Tagged<HeapObject> object) {
2774 if (strong_gc_subroot_names_.empty()) {
2775 Isolate* isolate = Isolate::FromHeap(heap_);
2776 for (RootIndex root_index = RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot;
2777 root_index <= RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot; ++root_index) {
2778 const char* name = RootsTable::name(root_index);
2779 Tagged<Object> root = isolate->root(root_index);
2780 CHECK(!IsSmi(root));
2781 strong_gc_subroot_names_.emplace(Cast<HeapObject>(root), name);
2782 }
2783 CHECK(!strong_gc_subroot_names_.empty());
2784 }
2785 auto it = strong_gc_subroot_names_.find(object);
2786 return it != strong_gc_subroot_names_.end() ? it->second : nullptr;
2787}
2788
2789void V8HeapExplorer::TagObject(Tagged<Object> obj, const char* tag,
2790 std::optional<HeapEntry::Type> type,
2791 bool overwrite_existing_name) {
2792 if (IsEssentialObject(obj)) {
2793 HeapEntry* entry = GetEntry(obj);
2794 if (overwrite_existing_name || entry->name()[0] == '\0') {
2795 entry->set_name(tag);
2796 }
2797 if (type.has_value()) {
2798 entry->set_type(*type);
2799 }
2800 }
2801}
2802
2803void V8HeapExplorer::RecursivelyTagConstantPool(Tagged<Object> obj,
2804 const char* tag,
2805 HeapEntry::Type type,
2806 int recursion_limit) {
2807 --recursion_limit;
2808 if (IsFixedArrayExact(obj, isolate())) {
2809 Tagged<FixedArray> arr = Cast<FixedArray>(obj);
2810 TagObject(arr, tag, type);
2811 if (recursion_limit <= 0) return;
2812 for (int i = 0; i < arr->length(); ++i) {
2813 RecursivelyTagConstantPool(arr->get(i), tag, type, recursion_limit);
2814 }
2815 } else if (IsTrustedFixedArray(obj, isolate())) {
2816 Tagged<TrustedFixedArray> arr = Cast<TrustedFixedArray>(obj);
2817 TagObject(arr, tag, type, /*overwrite_existing_name=*/true);
2818 if (recursion_limit <= 0) return;
2819 for (int i = 0; i < arr->length(); ++i) {
2820 RecursivelyTagConstantPool(arr->get(i), tag, type, recursion_limit);
2821 }
2822 } else if (IsNameDictionary(obj, isolate()) ||
2823 IsNumberDictionary(obj, isolate())) {
2824 TagObject(obj, tag, type);
2825 }
2826}
2827
2828class GlobalObjectsEnumerator : public RootVisitor {
2829 public:
2830 GlobalObjectsEnumerator(Isolate* isolate,
2831 std::function<void(Handle<JSGlobalObject>)> handler)
2832 : isolate_(isolate), handler_(handler) {}
2833
2834 void VisitRootPointers(Root root, const char* description,
2835 FullObjectSlot start, FullObjectSlot end) override {
2836 VisitRootPointersImpl(root, description, start, end);
2837 }
2838
2839 void VisitRootPointers(Root root, const char* description,
2840 OffHeapObjectSlot start,
2841 OffHeapObjectSlot end) override {
2842 VisitRootPointersImpl(root, description, start, end);
2843 }
2844
2845 private:
2846 template <typename TSlot>
2847 void VisitRootPointersImpl(Root root, const char* description, TSlot start,
2848 TSlot end) {
2849 for (TSlot p = start; p < end; ++p) {
2850 DCHECK(!MapWord::IsPacked(p.Relaxed_Load(isolate_).ptr()));
2851 Tagged<Object> o = p.load(isolate_);
2852 if (!IsNativeContext(o, isolate_)) continue;
2853 Tagged<JSObject> proxy = Cast<Context>(o)->global_proxy();
2854 if (!IsJSGlobalProxy(proxy, isolate_)) continue;
2855 Tagged<Object> global = proxy->map(isolate_)->prototype(isolate_);
2856 if (!IsJSGlobalObject(global, isolate_)) continue;
2857 handler_(handle(Cast<JSGlobalObject>(global), isolate_));
2858 }
2859 }
2860
2861 Isolate* isolate_;
2862 std::function<void(Handle<JSGlobalObject>)> handler_;
2863};
2864
2865V8HeapExplorer::TemporaryGlobalObjectTags
2866V8HeapExplorer::CollectTemporaryGlobalObjectsTags() {
2867 if (!global_object_name_resolver_) return {};
2868
2869 Isolate* isolate = heap_->isolate();
2870 TemporaryGlobalObjectTags global_object_tags;
2871 HandleScope scope(isolate);
2872 GlobalObjectsEnumerator enumerator(
2873 isolate, [this, isolate, &global_object_tags](
2874 DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object) {
2875 if (const char* tag = global_object_name_resolver_->GetName(
2876 Utils::ToLocal(Cast<JSObject>(global_object)))) {
2877 global_object_tags.emplace_back(
2878 Global<v8::Object>(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(isolate),
2879 Utils::ToLocal(Cast<JSObject>(global_object))),
2880 tag);
2881 global_object_tags.back().first.SetWeak();
2882 }
2883 });
2884 isolate->global_handles()->IterateAllRoots(&enumerator);
2885 isolate->traced_handles()->Iterate(&enumerator);
2886 return global_object_tags;
2887}
2888
2889void V8HeapExplorer::MakeGlobalObjectTagMap(
2890 TemporaryGlobalObjectTags&& global_object_tags) {
2891 HandleScope scope(heap_->isolate());
2892 for (const auto& pair : global_object_tags) {
2893 if (!pair.first.IsEmpty()) {
2894 // Temporary local.
2895 auto local = Utils::OpenPersistent(pair.first);
2896 global_object_tag_map_.emplace(Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*local), pair.second);
2897 }
2898 }

2901class EmbedderGraphImpl : public EmbedderGraph {
2902 public:
2903 struct Edge {
2904 Node* from;
2905 Node* to;
2906 const char* name;
2907 };
2908
2909 class V8NodeImpl : public Node {
2910 public:
2911 explicit V8NodeImpl(Tagged<Object> object) : object_(object) {}
2912 Tagged<Object> GetObject() { return object_; }
2913
2914 // Node overrides.
2915 bool IsEmbedderNode() override { return false; }
2916 const char* Name() override {
2917 // The name should be retrieved via GetObject().
2918 UNREACHABLE();
2919 }
2920 size_t SizeInBytes() override {
2921 // The size should be retrieved via GetObject().
2922 UNREACHABLE();
2923 }
2924
2925 private:
2926 Tagged<Object> object_;
2927 };
2928
2929 Node* V8Node(const v8::Local<v8::Value>& value) final {
2930 v8::Local<v8::Data> data = value;
2931 return V8Node(data);
2932 }

2934 Node* V8Node(const v8::Local<v8::Data>& data) final {
2935 DirectHandle<Object> object = v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*data);
2936 DCHECK(!object.is_null());
2937 return AddNode(std::unique_ptr<Node>(new V8NodeImpl(*object)));
2938 }
2939
2940 Node* AddNode(std::unique_ptr<Node> node) final {
2941 Node* result = node.get();

2943 return result;
2944 }

2946 void AddEdge(Node* from, Node* to, const char* name) final {
2947 edges_.push_back({from, to, name});
2948 }
2949
2950 const std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Node>>& nodes() { return nodes_; }
2951 const std::vector<Edge>& edges() { return edges_; }
2952
2953 private:

2956};

2975const char* EmbedderGraphNodeName(StringsStorage* names,
2976 EmbedderGraphImpl::Node* node) {
2977 const char* prefix = node->NamePrefix();
2978 return prefix ? names->GetFormatted("%s %s", prefix, node->Name())
2979 : names->GetCopy(node->Name());
2980}
2981
2982HeapEntry::Type EmbedderGraphNodeType(EmbedderGraphImpl::Node* node) {
2983 return node->IsRootNode() ? HeapEntry::kSynthetic : HeapEntry::kNative;
2984}
2985
2986// Merges the names of an embedder node and its wrapper node.
2987// If the wrapper node name contains a tag suffix (part after '/') then the
2988// result is the embedder node name concatenated with the tag suffix.
2989// Otherwise, the result is the embedder node name.
2990const char* MergeNames(StringsStorage* names, const char* embedder_name,
2991 const char* wrapper_name) {
2992 const char* suffix = strchr(wrapper_name, '/');
2993 return suffix ? names->GetFormatted("%s %s", embedder_name, suffix)
2994 : embedder_name;
2995}

2998
2999HeapEntry* EmbedderGraphEntriesAllocator::AllocateEntry(HeapThing ptr) {
3000 EmbedderGraphImpl::Node* node =
3001 reinterpret_cast<EmbedderGraphImpl::Node*>(ptr);
3002 DCHECK(node->IsEmbedderNode());
3003 size_t size = node->SizeInBytes();
3004 Address lookup_address = reinterpret_cast<Address>(node->GetNativeObject());
3005 HeapObjectsMap::MarkEntryAccessed accessed =
3006 HeapObjectsMap::MarkEntryAccessed::kYes;
3007 HeapObjectsMap::IsNativeObject is_native_object =
3008 HeapObjectsMap::IsNativeObject::kNo;
3009 if (!lookup_address) {
3010 // If there is not a native object associated with this embedder object,
3011 // then request the address of the embedder object.
3012 lookup_address = reinterpret_cast<Address>(node->GetAddress());
3013 is_native_object = HeapObjectsMap::IsNativeObject::kYes;
3014 }
3015 if (!lookup_address) {
3016 // If the Node implementation did not provide either a native address or an
3017 // embedder address, then use the address of the Node itself for the lookup.
3018 // In this case, we'll set the "accessed" flag on the newly created
3019 // HeapEntry to false, to indicate that this entry should not persist for
3020 // future snapshots.
3021 lookup_address = reinterpret_cast<Address>(node);
3022 accessed = HeapObjectsMap::MarkEntryAccessed::kNo;
3023 }
3024 SnapshotObjectId id = heap_object_map_->FindOrAddEntry(
3025 lookup_address, 0, accessed, is_native_object);
3026 auto* heap_entry = snapshot_->AddEntry(EmbedderGraphNodeType(node),
3027 EmbedderGraphNodeName(names_, node),
3028 id, static_cast<int>(size), 0);
3029 heap_entry->set_detachedness(node->GetDetachedness());
3030 return heap_entry;
3031}
3032
3033HeapEntry* EmbedderGraphEntriesAllocator::AllocateEntry(Tagged<Smi> smi) {
3034 DCHECK(false);
3035 return nullptr;
3036}

3047
3048void NativeObjectsExplorer::MergeNodeIntoEntry(
3049 HeapEntry* entry, EmbedderGraph::Node* original_node,
3050 EmbedderGraph::Node* wrapper_node) {
3051 // The wrapper node may be an embedder node (for testing purposes) or a V8
3052 // node (production code).
3053 if (!wrapper_node->IsEmbedderNode()) {
3054 // For V8 nodes only we can add a lookup.
3055 EmbedderGraphImpl::V8NodeImpl* v8_node =
3056 static_cast<EmbedderGraphImpl::V8NodeImpl*>(wrapper_node);
3057 Tagged<Object> object = v8_node->GetObject();
3058 DCHECK(!IsSmi(object));
3059 if (original_node->GetNativeObject()) {
3060 Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object = Cast<HeapObject>(object);
3061 heap_object_map_->AddMergedNativeEntry(original_node->GetNativeObject(),
3062 heap_object.address());
3063 DCHECK_EQ(entry->id(), heap_object_map_->FindMergedNativeEntry(
3064 original_node->GetNativeObject()));
3065 }
3066 }
3067 entry->set_detachedness(original_node->GetDetachedness());
3068 entry->set_name(MergeNames(
3069 names_, EmbedderGraphNodeName(names_, original_node), entry->name()));
3070 entry->set_type(EmbedderGraphNodeType(original_node));
3071 DCHECK_GE(entry->self_size() + original_node->SizeInBytes(),
3072 entry->self_size());
3073 entry->add_self_size(original_node->SizeInBytes());
3074}
3075
3076HeapEntry* NativeObjectsExplorer::EntryForEmbedderGraphNode(
3077 EmbedderGraphImpl::Node* node) {
3078 // Return the entry for the wrapper node if present.
3079 if (node->WrapperNode()) {
3080 node = node->WrapperNode();
3081 }
3082 // Node is EmbedderNode.
3083 if (node->IsEmbedderNode()) {
3084 return generator_->FindOrAddEntry(node,
3085 embedder_graph_entries_allocator_.get());
3086 }
3087 // Node is V8NodeImpl.
3088 Tagged<Object> object =
3089 static_cast<EmbedderGraphImpl::V8NodeImpl*>(node)->GetObject();
3090 if (IsSmi(object)) return nullptr;
3091 auto* entry = generator_->FindEntry(
3092 reinterpret_cast<void*>(Cast<Object>(object).ptr()));
3093 return entry;
3094}
3095
3096bool NativeObjectsExplorer::IterateAndExtractReferences(
3097 HeapSnapshotGenerator* generator) {
3098 generator_ = generator;
3099
3100 if (v8_flags.heap_profiler_use_embedder_graph &&
3101 snapshot_->profiler()->HasBuildEmbedderGraphCallback()) {
3102 v8::HandleScope scope(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(isolate_));
3103 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3104 EmbedderGraphImpl graph;
3105 snapshot_->profiler()->BuildEmbedderGraph(isolate_, &graph);
3106 for (const auto& node : graph.nodes()) {
3107 // Only add embedder nodes as V8 nodes have been added already by the
3108 // V8HeapExplorer.
3109 if (!node->IsEmbedderNode()) continue;
3110
3111 if (auto* entry = EntryForEmbedderGraphNode(node.get())) {
3112 if (node->IsRootNode()) {
3113 snapshot_->root()->SetIndexedAutoIndexReference(
3114 HeapGraphEdge::kElement, entry, generator_,
3115 HeapEntry::kOffHeapPointer);
3116 }
3117 if (node->WrapperNode()) {
3118 MergeNodeIntoEntry(entry, node.get(), node->WrapperNode());
3119 }
3120 }
3121 }
3122 // Fill edges of the graph.
3123 for (const auto& edge : graph.edges()) {
3124 // |from| and |to| can be nullptr if the corresponding node is a V8 node
3125 // pointing to a Smi.
3126 HeapEntry* from = EntryForEmbedderGraphNode(edge.from);
3127 if (!from) continue;
3128 HeapEntry* to = EntryForEmbedderGraphNode(edge.to);
3129 if (!to) continue;
3130 if (edge.name == nullptr) {
3131 from->SetIndexedAutoIndexReference(HeapGraphEdge::kElement, to,
3132 generator_,
3133 HeapEntry::kOffHeapPointer);
3134 } else {
3135 from->SetNamedReference(HeapGraphEdge::kInternal,
3136 names_->GetCopy(edge.name), to, generator_,
3137 HeapEntry::kOffHeapPointer);
3138 }
3139 }
3140 }
3141 generator_ = nullptr;
3142 return true;
3143}

3158 public:
3159 explicit NullContextForSnapshotScope(Isolate* isolate)
3160 : isolate_(isolate), prev_(isolate->context()) {
3161 isolate_->set_context(Context());
3162 }

3167 Tagged<Context> prev_;

3170
3171bool HeapSnapshotGenerator::GenerateSnapshot() {
3172 v8::base::ElapsedTimer timer;
3173 timer.Start();
3174
3175 IsolateSafepointScope scope(heap_);
3176
3177 Isolate* isolate = heap_->isolate();
3178 auto temporary_global_object_tags =
3179 v8_heap_explorer_.CollectTemporaryGlobalObjectsTags();
3180
3181 EmbedderStackStateScope stack_scope(
3182 heap_, EmbedderStackStateOrigin::kImplicitThroughTask, stack_state_);
3183 heap_->CollectAllAvailableGarbage(GarbageCollectionReason::kHeapProfiler);
3184
3185 // No allocation that could trigger GC from here onwards. We cannot use a
3186 // DisallowGarbageCollection scope as the HeapObjectIterator used during
3187 // snapshot creation enters a safepoint as well. However, in practice we
3188 // already enter a safepoint above so that should never trigger a GC.
3189 DisallowPositionInfoSlow no_position_info_slow;
3190
3191 NullContextForSnapshotScope null_context_scope(isolate);
3192
3193 v8_heap_explorer_.MakeGlobalObjectTagMap(
3194 std::move(temporary_global_object_tags));
3195
3196 InitProgressCounter();
3197
3198 snapshot_->AddSyntheticRootEntries();
3199
3200 v8_heap_explorer_.PopulateLineEnds();
3201 if (!FillReferences()) return false;
3202
3203 snapshot_->FillChildren();
3204 snapshot_->RememberLastJSObjectId();
3205
3206 progress_counter_ = progress_total_;
3207
3208 if (i::v8_flags.profile_heap_snapshot) {
3209 base::OS::PrintError("[Heap snapshot took %0.3f ms]\n",
3210 timer.Elapsed().InMillisecondsF());
3211 }
3212 timer.Stop();
3213 if (!ProgressReport(true)) return false;
3214 return true;
3215}
3216
3217bool HeapSnapshotGenerator::GenerateSnapshotAfterGC() {
3218 // Same as above, but no allocations, no GC run, and no progress report.
3219 IsolateSafepointScope scope(heap_);
3220 auto temporary_global_object_tags =
3221 v8_heap_explorer_.CollectTemporaryGlobalObjectsTags();
3222 NullContextForSnapshotScope null_context_scope(heap_->isolate());
3223 v8_heap_explorer_.MakeGlobalObjectTagMap(
3224 std::move(temporary_global_object_tags));
3225 snapshot_->AddSyntheticRootEntries();
3226 v8_heap_explorer_.PopulateLineEnds();
3227 if (!FillReferences()) return false;
3228 snapshot_->FillChildren();
3229 snapshot_->RememberLastJSObjectId();
3230 return true;
3231}
3232
3233void HeapSnapshotGenerator::ProgressStep() {
3234 // Only increment the progress_counter_ until
3235 // equal to progress_total -1 == progress_counter.
3236 // This ensures that intermediate ProgressReport calls will never signal
3237 // that the work is finished (i.e. progress_counter_ == progress_total_).
3238 // Only the forced ProgressReport() at the end of GenerateSnapshot() should,
3239 // after setting progress_counter_ = progress_total_, signal that the
3240 // work is finished because signalling finished twice
3241 // breaks the DevTools frontend.
3242 if (control_ != nullptr && progress_total_ > progress_counter_ + 1) {
3243 ++progress_counter_;
3244 }
3245}
3246
3247bool HeapSnapshotGenerator::ProgressReport(bool force) {
3248 const int kProgressReportGranularity = 10000;
3249 if (control_ != nullptr &&
3250 (force || progress_counter_ % kProgressReportGranularity == 0)) {
3251 return control_->ReportProgressValue(progress_counter_, progress_total_) ==
3252 v8::ActivityControl::kContinue;
3253 }
3254 return true;
3255}
3256
3257void HeapSnapshotGenerator::InitProgressCounter() {
3258 if (control_ == nullptr) return;
3259 progress_total_ = v8_heap_explorer_.EstimateObjectsCount();
3260 progress_counter_ = 0;
3261}
3262
3263bool HeapSnapshotGenerator::FillReferences() {
3264 return v8_heap_explorer_.IterateAndExtractReferences(this) &&
3265 dom_explorer_.IterateAndExtractReferences(this);
3266}

3272void HeapSnapshotJSONSerializer::Serialize(v8::OutputStream* stream) {

3274 timer.Start();

3276 writer_ = new OutputStreamWriter(stream);
3277 trace_function_count_ = 0;

3279 snapshot_->profiler()->allocation_tracker()) {
3280 trace_function_count_ =

3282 }
3283 SerializeImpl();
3284 delete writer_;
3285 writer_ = nullptr;
3286
3287 if (i::v8_flags.profile_heap_snapshot) {
3288 base::OS::PrintError("[Serialization of heap snapshot took %0.3f ms]\n",
3289 timer.Elapsed().InMillisecondsF());

3294void HeapSnapshotJSONSerializer::SerializeImpl() {
3295 DCHECK_EQ(0, snapshot_->root()->index());
3296 writer_->AddCharacter('{');
3297 writer_->AddString("\"snapshot\":{");
3298 SerializeSnapshot();
3299 if (writer_->aborted()) return;
3300 writer_->AddString("},\n");
3301 writer_->AddString("\"nodes\":[");
3302 SerializeNodes();
3303 if (writer_->aborted()) return;
3304 writer_->AddString("],\n");
3305 writer_->AddString("\"edges\":[");
3306 SerializeEdges();
3307 if (writer_->aborted()) return;
3308 writer_->AddString("],\n");
3309
3310 writer_->AddString("\"trace_function_infos\":[");
3311 SerializeTraceNodeInfos();
3312 if (writer_->aborted()) return;
3313 writer_->AddString("],\n");
3314 writer_->AddString("\"trace_tree\":[");
3315 SerializeTraceTree();
3316 if (writer_->aborted()) return;
3317 writer_->AddString("],\n");
3318
3319 writer_->AddString("\"samples\":[");
3320 SerializeSamples();
3321 if (writer_->aborted()) return;
3322 writer_->AddString("],\n");
3323
3324 writer_->AddString("\"locations\":[");
3325 SerializeLocations();
3326 if (writer_->aborted()) return;
3327 writer_->AddString("],\n");
3328
3329 writer_->AddString("\"strings\":[");
3330 SerializeStrings();
3331 if (writer_->aborted()) return;
3332 writer_->AddCharacter(']');
3333 writer_->AddCharacter('}');
3334 writer_->Finalize();
3335}

3337int HeapSnapshotJSONSerializer::GetStringId(const char* s) {
3338 base::HashMap::Entry* cache_entry =
3339 strings_.LookupOrInsert(const_cast<char*>(s), StringHash(s));
3340 if (cache_entry->value == nullptr) {
3341 cache_entry->value = reinterpret_cast<void*>(next_string_id_++);
3342 }
3343 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(cache_entry->value));
3344}

3346namespace {
3347
3348template <size_t size>
3349struct ToUnsigned;
3350
3351template <>
3352struct ToUnsigned<1> {
3353 using Type = uint8_t;
3354};
3355
3356template <>
3357struct ToUnsigned<4> {
3358 using Type = uint32_t;
3359};
3360
3361template <>
3362struct ToUnsigned<8> {
3363 using Type = uint64_t;
3364};
3365
3366} // namespace
3367
3368template <typename T>
3369static int utoa_impl(T value, base::Vector<char> buffer, int buffer_pos) {
3370 static_assert(static_cast<T>(-1) > 0); // Check that T is unsigned
3371 int number_of_digits = 0;
3372 T t = value;
3373 do {
3374 ++number_of_digits;
3375 } while (t /= 10);
3376
3377 buffer_pos += number_of_digits;
3378 int result = buffer_pos;
3379 do {
3380 int last_digit = static_cast<int>(value % 10);
3381 buffer[--buffer_pos] = '0' + last_digit;
3382 value /= 10;
3383 } while (value);
3384 return result;
3385}
3386
3387template <typename T>
3388static int utoa(T value, base::Vector<char> buffer, int buffer_pos) {
3389 typename ToUnsigned<sizeof(value)>::Type unsigned_value = value;
3390 static_assert(sizeof(value) == sizeof(unsigned_value));
3391 return utoa_impl(unsigned_value, buffer, buffer_pos);
3392}
3393
3394void HeapSnapshotJSONSerializer::SerializeEdge(HeapGraphEdge* edge,
3395 bool first_edge) {
3396 // The buffer needs space for 3 unsigned ints, 3 commas, \n and \0
3397 static const int kBufferSize =
3398 MaxDecimalDigitsIn<sizeof(unsigned)>::kUnsigned * 3 + 3 + 2;
3399 base::EmbeddedVector<char, kBufferSize> buffer;
3400 int edge_name_or_index = edge->type() == HeapGraphEdge::kElement ||
3401 edge->type() == HeapGraphEdge::kHidden
3402 ? edge->index()
3403 : GetStringId(edge->name());
3404 int buffer_pos = 0;
3405 if (!first_edge) {
3406 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3407 }
3408 buffer_pos = utoa(edge->type(), buffer, buffer_pos);
3409 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3410 buffer_pos = utoa(edge_name_or_index, buffer, buffer_pos);
3411 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3412 buffer_pos = utoa(to_node_index(edge->to()), buffer, buffer_pos);
3413 buffer[buffer_pos++] = '\n';
3414 buffer[buffer_pos++] = '\0';
3415 writer_->AddString(buffer.begin());
3416}
3417
3418void HeapSnapshotJSONSerializer::SerializeEdges() {
3419 std::vector<HeapGraphEdge*>& edges = snapshot_->children();
3420 for (size_t i = 0; i < edges.size(); ++i) {
3421 DCHECK(i == 0 ||
3422 edges[i - 1]->from()->index() <= edges[i]->from()->index());
3423 SerializeEdge(edges[i], i == 0);
3424 if (writer_->aborted()) return;
3425 }
3426}
3427
3428void HeapSnapshotJSONSerializer::SerializeNode(const HeapEntry* entry) {
3429 // The buffer needs space for 5 unsigned ints, 1 size_t, 1 uint8_t, 7 commas,
3430 // \n and \0
3431 static const int kBufferSize =
3432 5 * MaxDecimalDigitsIn<sizeof(unsigned)>::kUnsigned +
3433 MaxDecimalDigitsIn<sizeof(size_t)>::kUnsigned +
3434 MaxDecimalDigitsIn<sizeof(uint8_t)>::kUnsigned + 7 + 1 + 1;
3435 base::EmbeddedVector<char, kBufferSize> buffer;
3436 int buffer_pos = 0;
3437 if (to_node_index(entry) != 0) {
3438 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3439 }
3440 buffer_pos = utoa(entry->type(), buffer, buffer_pos);
3441 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3442 buffer_pos = utoa(GetStringId(entry->name()), buffer, buffer_pos);
3443 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3444 buffer_pos = utoa(entry->id(), buffer, buffer_pos);
3445 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3446 buffer_pos = utoa(entry->self_size(), buffer, buffer_pos);
3447 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3448 buffer_pos = utoa(entry->children_count(), buffer, buffer_pos);
3449 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3450 if (trace_function_count_) {
3451 buffer_pos = utoa(entry->trace_node_id(), buffer, buffer_pos);
3452 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3453 } else {
3454 CHECK_EQ(0, entry->trace_node_id());
3455 }
3456 buffer_pos = utoa(entry->detachedness(), buffer, buffer_pos);
3457 buffer[buffer_pos++] = '\n';
3458 buffer[buffer_pos++] = '\0';
3459 writer_->AddString(buffer.begin());
3460}
3461
3462void HeapSnapshotJSONSerializer::SerializeNodes() {
3463 const std::deque<HeapEntry>& entries = snapshot_->entries();
3464 for (const HeapEntry& entry : entries) {
3465 SerializeNode(&entry);
3466 if (writer_->aborted()) return;
3467 }
3468}

3560static void WriteUChar(OutputStreamWriter* w, unibrow::uchar u) {
3561 static const char hex_chars[] = "0123456789ABCDEF";
3562 w->AddString("\\u");
3563 w->AddCharacter(hex_chars[(u >> 12) & 0xF]);
3564 w->AddCharacter(hex_chars[(u >> 8) & 0xF]);
3565 w->AddCharacter(hex_chars[(u >> 4) & 0xF]);
3566 w->AddCharacter(hex_chars[u & 0xF]);
3567}

3575
3576void HeapSnapshotJSONSerializer::SerializeTraceNode(AllocationTraceNode* node) {
3577 // The buffer needs space for 4 unsigned ints, 4 commas, [ and \0
3578 const int kBufferSize =
3579 4 * MaxDecimalDigitsIn<sizeof(unsigned)>::kUnsigned + 4 + 1 + 1;
3580 base::EmbeddedVector<char, kBufferSize> buffer;
3581 int buffer_pos = 0;
3582 buffer_pos = utoa(node->id(), buffer, buffer_pos);
3583 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3584 buffer_pos = utoa(node->function_info_index(), buffer, buffer_pos);
3585 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3586 buffer_pos = utoa(node->allocation_count(), buffer, buffer_pos);
3587 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3588 buffer_pos = utoa(node->allocation_size(), buffer, buffer_pos);
3589 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3590 buffer[buffer_pos++] = '[';
3591 buffer[buffer_pos++] = '\0';
3592 writer_->AddString(buffer.begin());
3593
3594 int i = 0;
3595 for (AllocationTraceNode* child : node->children()) {
3596 if (i++ > 0) {
3597 writer_->AddCharacter(',');
3598 }
3599 SerializeTraceNode(child);
3600 }
3601 writer_->AddCharacter(']');
3602}
3603
3604// 0-based position is converted to 1-based during the serialization.
3605static int SerializePosition(int position, base::Vector<char> buffer,
3606 int buffer_pos) {
3607 if (position == -1) {
3608 buffer[buffer_pos++] = '0';
3609 } else {
3610 DCHECK_GE(position, 0);
3611 buffer_pos = utoa(static_cast<unsigned>(position + 1), buffer, buffer_pos);
3612 }
3613 return buffer_pos;
3614}

3616void HeapSnapshotJSONSerializer::SerializeTraceNodeInfos() {
3617 AllocationTracker* tracker = snapshot_->profiler()->allocation_tracker();
3618 if (!tracker) return;
3619 // The buffer needs space for 6 unsigned ints, 6 commas, \n and \0
3620 const int kBufferSize =
3621 6 * MaxDecimalDigitsIn<sizeof(unsigned)>::kUnsigned + 6 + 1 + 1;
3622 base::EmbeddedVector<char, kBufferSize> buffer;
3623 int i = 0;
3624 for (AllocationTracker::FunctionInfo* info : tracker->function_info_list()) {
3625 int buffer_pos = 0;
3626 if (i++ > 0) {
3627 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3628 }
3629 buffer_pos = utoa(info->function_id, buffer, buffer_pos);
3630 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3631 buffer_pos = utoa(GetStringId(info->name), buffer, buffer_pos);
3632 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3633 buffer_pos = utoa(GetStringId(info->script_name), buffer, buffer_pos);
3634 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3635 // The cast is safe because script id is a non-negative Smi.
3636 buffer_pos =
3637 utoa(static_cast<unsigned>(info->script_id), buffer, buffer_pos);
3638 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3639 buffer_pos = SerializePosition(info->line, buffer, buffer_pos);
3640 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3641 buffer_pos = SerializePosition(info->column, buffer, buffer_pos);
3642 buffer[buffer_pos++] = '\n';
3643 buffer[buffer_pos++] = '\0';
3644 writer_->AddString(buffer.begin());
3645 }
3646}
3647
3648void HeapSnapshotJSONSerializer::SerializeSamples() {
3649 const std::vector<HeapObjectsMap::TimeInterval>& samples =
3650 snapshot_->profiler()->heap_object_map()->samples();
3651 if (samples.empty()) return;
3652 base::TimeTicks start_time = samples[0].timestamp;
3653 // The buffer needs space for 2 unsigned ints, 2 commas, \n and \0
3654 const int kBufferSize = MaxDecimalDigitsIn<sizeof(
3655 base::TimeDelta().InMicroseconds())>::kUnsigned +
3656 MaxDecimalDigitsIn<sizeof(samples[0].id)>::kUnsigned +
3657 2 + 1 + 1;
3658 base::EmbeddedVector<char, kBufferSize> buffer;
3659 int i = 0;
3660 for (const HeapObjectsMap::TimeInterval& sample : samples) {
3661 int buffer_pos = 0;
3662 if (i++ > 0) {
3663 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3664 }
3665 base::TimeDelta time_delta = sample.timestamp - start_time;
3666 buffer_pos = utoa(time_delta.InMicroseconds(), buffer, buffer_pos);
3667 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3668 buffer_pos = utoa(sample.last_assigned_id(), buffer, buffer_pos);
3669 buffer[buffer_pos++] = '\n';
3670 buffer[buffer_pos++] = '\0';
3671 writer_->AddString(buffer.begin());
3672 }
3673}
3674
3675void HeapSnapshotJSONSerializer::SerializeString(const unsigned char* s) {
3676 writer_->AddCharacter('\n');
3677 writer_->AddCharacter('\"');
3678 for (; *s != '\0'; ++s) {
3679 switch (*s) {
3680 case '\b':
3681 writer_->AddString("\\b");
3682 continue;
3683 case '\f':
3684 writer_->AddString("\\f");
3685 continue;
3686 case '\n':
3687 writer_->AddString("\\n");
3688 continue;
3689 case '\r':
3690 writer_->AddString("\\r");
3691 continue;
3692 case '\t':
3693 writer_->AddString("\\t");
3694 continue;
3695 case '\"':
3696 case '\\':
3697 writer_->AddCharacter('\\');
3698 writer_->AddCharacter(*s);
3699 continue;
3700 default:
3701 if (*s > 31 && *s < 128) {
3702 writer_->AddCharacter(*s);
3703 } else if (*s <= 31) {
3704 // Special character with no dedicated literal.
3705 WriteUChar(writer_, *s);
3706 } else {
3707 // Convert UTF-8 into \u UTF-16 literal.
3708 size_t length = 1, cursor = 0;
3709 for (; length <= 4 && *(s + length) != '\0'; ++length) {
3710 }
3711 unibrow::uchar c = unibrow::Utf8::CalculateValue(s, length, &cursor);
3712 if (c != unibrow::Utf8::kBadChar) {
3713 WriteUChar(writer_, c);
3714 DCHECK_NE(cursor, 0);
3715 s += cursor - 1;
3716 } else {
3717 writer_->AddCharacter('?');
3718 }
3719 }
3720 }
3721 }
3722 writer_->AddCharacter('\"');
3723}
3724
3725void HeapSnapshotJSONSerializer::SerializeStrings() {
3726 base::ScopedVector<const unsigned char*> sorted_strings(strings_.occupancy() +
3727 1);
3728 for (base::HashMap::Entry* entry = strings_.Start(); entry != nullptr;
3729 entry = strings_.Next(entry)) {
3730 int index = static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(entry->value));
3731 sorted_strings[index] = reinterpret_cast<const unsigned char*>(entry->key);
3732 }
3733 writer_->AddString("\"<dummy>\"");
3734 for (int i = 1; i < sorted_strings.length(); ++i) {
3735 writer_->AddCharacter(',');
3736 SerializeString(sorted_strings[i]);
3737 if (writer_->aborted()) return;
3738 }
3739}

3741void HeapSnapshotJSONSerializer::SerializeLocation(
3742 const EntrySourceLocation& location) {
3743 // The buffer needs space for 4 unsigned ints, 3 commas, \n and \0
3744 static const int kBufferSize =
3745 MaxDecimalDigitsIn<sizeof(unsigned)>::kUnsigned * 4 + 3 + 2;
3746 base::EmbeddedVector<char, kBufferSize> buffer;
3747 int buffer_pos = 0;
3748 buffer_pos = utoa(to_node_index(location.entry_index), buffer, buffer_pos);
3749 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3750 buffer_pos = utoa(location.scriptId, buffer, buffer_pos);
3751 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3752 buffer_pos = utoa(location.line, buffer, buffer_pos);
3753 buffer[buffer_pos++] = ',';
3754 buffer_pos = utoa(location.col, buffer, buffer_pos);
3755 buffer[buffer_pos++] = '\n';
3756 buffer[buffer_pos++] = '\0';
3757 writer_->AddString(buffer.begin());
3758}
